title: nibble mix
directions: Combine cereals, pretzels and nuts in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt margarine; add the Worcestershire sauce, paprika and onion powder to margarine.
Pour over cereal mixture, tossing until well coated.

title: mama's meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, chopped onion, egg and minced garlic.
Roll into small balls and fry until brown.
Drain fat. Mix golden mushroom soup, chopped tomatoes, vinegar, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles or great for meatball hoagies.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Mix crumbs and poppy seed with butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: one bowl brownie recipe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl at High for 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate.
Mix in eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out fudgy.
Cool in pan; cut into squares.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados and mix with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
Spread bean dip in 9 x 13 pan.
Spread avocado mix over bean dip.
Spread taco mix next. Sprinkle in order onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
In a medium saucepan combine dry pudding mix and dry milk powder.
Add enough water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1 and 1/2 cups liquid.
Add liquid to dry pudding mixture and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla extract and cooked macaroni.
Mix gently to combine.
Cool 10 minutes.
Fold in Mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Pour into medium bowl.
Cover and cool at least 1 hour.
Fold in Cool Whip lite and marshmallows.
Chill until ready to serve.
This makes eight servings. of 2/3 cup.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add thawed strawberries and other ingredients.
Stir just enough to mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Put all of this in a long baking dish. Bake, covered with foil, for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 45 to 60 minutes longer.

title: souper sammich("a cabin fever treat")
directions: Spread butter on bread.
Cut cheese into slices and lay on bread.
Melt cheese on bread on toaster oven.
Eat with soup of choice.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute cabbage, onion, celery and carrots with 1 stick margarine or butter.
Add bouillon cubes, potatoes and water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Cut up 2 pound Velveeta cheese and cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: fresh mango chutney
directions: Thinly slice the mangoes and place in a bowl with remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Transfer to a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Stir occasionally so that mixture does not stick. Let cool before serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease or spray a 13 x 9 x 2 1/4-inch cake pan.
Mix coconut and pecans.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as instructed on the box.
Pour cake mix over pecans and coconut. Set aside.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Thorough mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add milk slowly so as not to lump.
Add 3 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thick enough to stand rather firm when cooled.
Removed from heat.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Cool and then pour into baked pie crust. Cover with meringue and bake 10-15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit nut snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tightly covered container.
You may use your favorite diced fruits or nuts.
Will keep a long time.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 14 (1/4 cup) servings.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Mix apples and salt; let stand 15 minutes. Blend eggs and sugar. Add flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and soda. Blend with pastry blender. Add apple mixture and nuts. Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 450° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Check with toothpick.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix sausage with rest of ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer crushed taco chips, chicken pieces and green pepper.
Repeat layers.
Top with Doritos.
Mix soups together and spread on top.
Spread on the Cheddar cheese.
Spread drained Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday banana nut bread
directions: Combine first four ingredients, then combine the next 3 ingredients and add to banana mixture, stirring until well blended.
Add last 3 ingredients and spoon batter into greased and floured 8-1/2 x 4-1/2 x 3 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cover with aluminum foil last 15 minutes if needed to keep from getting too brown.
Yield one loaf.

title: dream rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add sugar and shortening, softened yeast and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Let rise until size is doubled.
Roll out and make into rolls.
Spread with melted butter or oleo and fold over.
Grease pan and top of rolls with oleo.
Let rise and bake at 450° for 8 minutes or until brown.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain vegetables and place all ingredients in large bowl.

title: cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter.
May have to mix a little with your hands.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Put this mixture on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle more powdered sugar on top.

title: chocolate crazy cake
directions: Blend all ingredients by hand (no electric mixer).
Use an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out dry.

title: baklava
directions: Boil all the ingredients for 20 minutes. Add 1/4 cup honey. Cool off.
Pour over hot baklava.

title: mrs. clara holste's white cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well. Add flour and water alternately, then beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian macaroni combination
directions: In a nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add onion, carrots, broccoli and green pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes, until onion is tender. Add macaroni to nonstick skillet and stir.
Add vinegar and fat-free Italian dressing.
Reduce heat and cook on low for about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: macaroni-vegetable salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and cool. Add Italian dressing and chill overnight.
A few hours before serving, add celery, onion, carrots, green pepper and cheese. When ready to serve, add sour cream and stir.

title: layer dish-meat and vegetable
directions: Mix juice from peas with mushroom soup.
Layer vegetables. Top with browned ground beef and pour soup over this.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: skillet steak
directions: Coat steak with flour; pound into beef.
Brown in oil in 10-inch skillet; push beef to side.
Cook and stir onion in same oil until tender; drain.
Use potato liquid plus water to equal 1 cup.
Mix liquid, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, pepper flakes, bouillon, salt, marjoram and pepper; pour over beef and onion. Cover; simmer until beef is tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Rinse frozen beans under cold water to separate.
Add potatoes, beans and pimentos to skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until beans are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in spread; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Combine the ingredients and pour over meat.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Place roast in roasting pan and brush with marinade.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 hours for rare roast.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown steak in butter or Crisco.
Add boiling water, bouillon cube and cornstarch.
Gradually add 1 cup water; cook slowly until tender and add more water if needed.
Steam cabbage, onion and celery.
Add Japanese mixed vegetables and water chestnuts.
Add soy sauce.
Mix all ingredients together and dip over steamed rice.

title: salad dressing for macaroni
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Pour over 1 pound cooked drained macaroni.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate in pan over low flame.
Using a large bowl, add all ingredients, including chocolate.
Mix on medium speed until well blended.
Pour into two 13 x 9-inch pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next four ingredients.
Measure and stir together dry ingredients.
Mix well and roll into balls the size of walnut.
Roll in sugar.
Put on cookie.
Dip bottom of a glass in sugar.
Flatten balls.
Bake at 350°.

title: layered potato 'n ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cover potatoes with water in medium bowl. Stir in salt.
Let stand uncovered 15 minutes.
Drain thoroughly. Layer half each of the potatoes, corn, bell pepper, onion, ham and cheese in ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Repeat.
Mix milk, margarine and egg.
Beat in baking mix, sugar, pepper and curry powder until smooth.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until top is golden brown and center is set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dreamy fruit salad
directions: Fold in sour cream and sugar; chill for several hours.
Mix well and serve.

title: french onion soup (vernon)
directions: Peel and slice very thinly the onions, separating the rings. Cook slowly, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Sprinkle with a generous teaspoon of flour and when this has been well blended, add a pint of water and a tablespoon of "Gourmet Edge" beef extract.
Bring to a boil.
Then lower heat and let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Taste.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat over medium heat.
Good in crock-pots!

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine soda with applesauce about 1 hour before mixing cake. Cream butter and sugar, then fold in ingredients.
Bake in 200° oven about 2 hours.
If cake is browning too soon, place a pan of water under the cake.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well (using electric mixer makes for creamier ice cream).
Pour into freezing container.
Add milk to fill line on can and stir.
Freeze.

title: pistachio pizzazz
directions: Use 2 cylinders of Ritz crackers from the box.
Add 1/2 cup of melted butter to crushed crackers.
Pat this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch freezer and ovenproof baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Make as much or as little as you like.
Wash mushrooms and place in a container large enough to enable you to completely cover all mushrooms with Italian dressing.
Marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Next day, heat mushrooms to a boil and return to refrigerator for another 24 hours.

title: rea's no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix juice as directed.
Add as needed melted marshmallows and oleo together.
Add all the rest and pack in a greased pan or whatever and set for awhile.
Add a can of coconut if wanted or whatever.
Tube pan works best.

title: tomato cheese pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in butter until crumbly.
Add water and stir until dough holds together.
Press into an ungreased 9 to 10-inch pie plate.
Pierce bottom with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake with orange glaze(lo-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with vegetable spray and set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, allspice and granulated sugar into a large mixing bowl. Add brown sugar.
Using your fingers, press out all lumps. Add nuts and toss well to dredge.

In a 1-quart measuring cup, mix egg substitute with oil, orange zest, vanilla, carrots and pineapple. Pour mixture into well made in the dry ingredients and stir just enough to mix. Batter will be thin and lumpy, but do not mix any more at this point or cake may be tough.
Pour batter into prepared loaf pan, spreading it well into the corners and smoothing top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until cake is springy to touch and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on a wire rack in the pan.
Invert the pan on rack, turn right side up and cool to room temperature.
Spread the glaze over top of cooled cake, letting excess run down the sides.
Let glaze harden several hours before cutting the cake.
Slice 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Makes 18 servings.

title: 30 minute soup
directions: Brown the ground beef in 2 cups of water in pot.
When down, put in 2 cups of water.
When down, put in beans, corn, hominy, tomato sauce, butter and seasoning to taste.
Cook until butter melts, then serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish. Cover with Old English cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until bubbling.

title: ramockie
directions: Slice the bacon into thirds.
Wrap each whole water chestnut with one slice of bacon and hold together with a round wooden toothpick.
Bake at 375° until bacon is cooked (crisp).
Drain off grease.

title: christmas rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Stir 3 times while cooking.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter; sprinkle crumbs over butter and pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs. Top evenly with remaining ingredients; press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in bowl and add everything except pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: a different stroganoff
directions: Saute beef and onions in oil.
Add mushrooms, consomme, Sauterne and seasonings.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add cooked noodles and sour cream.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Make a white sauce with the fat, flour and milk.
Add fowl, seasoned with celery salt, lemon juice, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cool.
Shape and dip into fine crumbs, then into eggs and again into crumbs.
Fry in deep fat (275° to 390°) from 2 to 5 minutes.

title: easy pepper steak
directions: Brown beef and a little garlic powder in olive oil until done.
Pour in jars of gravy and mix well.
Put in peppers, onions and chestnuts and simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes until veggies are soft.
Serve over rice.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put the chicken breasts in a small casserole dish.
Put pats of butter on the chicken.
Then shake salt, pepper and garlic salt on the chicken.
Cover the dish with foil.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine in order given.
Bake in buttered glass baking dish at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with lemon slices.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: company bread(prepare ahead for the big event)
directions: Melt butter, cream cheese and sharp cheese in saucepan over very low heat.
Stir until melted.
Cut rolls in about 1-inch slices (about 25).
Dip in cheese mixture and coat well.
Let excess drip off and place on cookie sheet.
Place in freezer at least 2 hours or until frozen.
Put in plastic bags and store in freezer.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix well white sugar, brown sugar, shortening, eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, soda, M&M's, nuts and chocolate chips.
Use ice cream scoop to form cookies.
Flatten slightly. (Add no flour.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Boil sugar and Karo just to a rolling boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour over Special K and mix well. Press in a baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits and spread over top.
When cool, cut in bars.

title: asparagus salad(no sugar)
directions: Mix gelatin according to directions.
Add vinegar and refrigerate until thickens.
Pour in other ingredients, except asparagus.
Fill salad mold with half of mixture.
Arrange asparagus on top.
Add remaining jello mixture.
Refrigerate to congeal.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine flour and coconut.
Melt butter, brown sugar and syrup. Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour and coconut mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon about 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Allow cookies to set a few minutes before placing on a paper towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes.
Meanwhile, brown ground beef with onion, garlic, salt and pepper in a large skillet over medium heat.
Drain off drippings.
Stir green beans, soup, mushrooms and milk into meat mixture.
Pour filling into 8-inch baking dish. Spread mashed potatoes evenly over top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and pie is heated through.

title: triple dipped treats
directions: You will also need 4 to 5 wooden sticks.

title: bean stew
directions: Add beans to boiling water.
Return to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and soak for 1 hour.
Return to boiling; add onion, ham and seasonings.
Boil, uncovered, for 5 minutes; then cover and boil gently until beans are almost tender, about 1 hour.
Add carrots and celery.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: salad of gold
directions: Put ingredients one after the other in a blender.
Blend after each ingredient.
Chill in mold until set.

title: egg nog
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture coats the back of a spoon.
Cool mixture. Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites, then fold in whipped cream.
Garnish with nutmeg. Chill.
Makes 20 cups.

title: coconut cheese pie
directions: Spread butter evenly over the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Press 1 1/3 cups of coconut into butter, forming a shell.

title: broccoli cheese soup]
directions: Blend soups and cheese until smooth in a large pot over low heat.
Add spinach and broccoli; simmer.

title: ham sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and fill buns.
Wrap each in foil. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: oyster cracker munchies
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers) and heat.
Pour over crackers in a flat pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 225°.
Stir occasionally. Cool and store airtight.

title: oriental meatball salad
directions: In bowl, combine eggs and milk; stir in bread crumbs, onion salt and pepper.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Shape into
3/4-inch meatballs.
Cook meatballs in hot cooking oil about 10 minutes or until done, turning frequently.
Drain off fat.
Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Add water to reserved juice to make 3/4 cup liquid.

title: nancy's chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and cut in pieces.
Layer chicken and broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and curry.
Place on top of chicken mixture.
Cover with 2 packages of almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party little smokies
directions: Mix mustard and brown sugar.
Add water, vinegar and tomato sauce.
Pour over smokies in covered casserole and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: granola bars
directions: Combine butter, sugar and syrup in medium pan.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat and add cereal; press into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and let set for 30 minutes.
Makes 18 bars.
Optional:
Raisins, coconuts, dried fruits or other favorites may be added.

title: avocado-cottage cheese dip
directions: Onion Dip:
Put into a mixing bowl 1/2 pint of sour cream; add 1 package onion soup mix.

title: sweet potato salad(real good and very unusual)
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Mix last three ingredients thoroughly and pour over the first mix.
Toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly.
Yields 6 big servings.

title: chip dip
directions: Drain olive pieces.
Place cottage cheese, olives and horseradish in blender. Blend until creamy.
Add horseradish to desired taste.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup pecans.
Roll in ball.
Top with 1/2 cup pecans.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: barb's quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with a small amount of egg.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Brown ground beef, sausage and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Spoon into pie shell.

title: buena's cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle paprika and little chili powder on wax paper.
Roll until rolls are covered.
Wrap in foil; store in refrigerator until firm.
Slice.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers; combine with margarine and sugar.
Line baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 5 minutes.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Place on top of graham cracker crust.
Top with cherries and refrigerate.

title: super easy spice cake
directions: In a medium size bowl, beat the 3 eggs until mixed.
Add dry cake mix and apple pie filling, breaking apple slices into 3 pieces.
Spray inside of microwave Bundt pan with vegetable spray. Pour batter in pan.
Bake in microwave for 15 minutes on High, turning 1/4 turn every 5 minutes.
Let cool about 15 minutes. Turn out onto cake plate.
Spread frosting while cake is slightly warm.
Serve.

title: ham dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a food processor.
Serve with Sociables crackers.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
While rice is cooking, brown the sausage, green pepper and onion (drain off any fat), then add the tomato sauce, then the spices.
Stir cooked rice and sausage together and pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Melt butter in an iron skillet.
Place 1 layer of cabbage, 1 layer of potatoes, sliced, 1 layer of onions, diced, and 1 layer of yellow squash.
Cook covered on top of stove on slow.
Check with fork every 10 minutes to test how it is cooking.
Cook for 30 minutes.
When done, top with Velveeta cheese and let simmer until melted.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Skin chicken; wash and dry it.
Line a pan with aluminum foil. Place chicken on foil.
Glaze chicken with mixture of all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Turn chicken over after 45 minutes and glaze other side.
Pour remaining glaze over chicken.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers; mix with oleo.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: gazpacho with cilantro
directions: Put tomatoes in a large bowl and break them up with a fork or your hands, removing any tough parts.
Add peppers, V-8 juice, water, onions, celery, oil, garlic, vinegar and cilantro.
Stir well and add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving. Serves 4 to 5.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook chops with onion for 10 minutes on each side.
Spoon off fat.
Stir soup and milk together in small bowl.
Pour over chops and cook 10 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add bell pepper and onion. Saute until tender.
Add shrimp, soup and dash of Tabasco sauce. Season to taste with Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pecan cups
directions: Cream together cream cheese and margarine; blend in flour and roll out.
Cut with fluted cutter (3-inch size).
Place in mini tart pans and add filling.
Following are various ways they can be filled.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all together; let set in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Keeps well.

title: date squares(diabetic)
directions: Combine water, dates, prunes and raisins. Boil 10 minutes or until water is absorbed. Add margarine and cool.
Mix eggs and vanilla; add to fruit mixture. Add flour, soda, sugar and spices. Mix well.
Spread in greased pan; sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix blueberries and 2 to 3 tablespoons of sugar in small bowl. Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat 1 egg with 1 cup of milk and 6 tablespoons of melted butter.
Add milk mix to dry mix.
Blend.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all ingredients and mix thoroughly with hands. Refrigerate overnight.

title: layered diablo dip
directions: In this recipe, ingredients are layered in circles on a large round platter.
Form bottom circle of the mashed avocados, dashed with salt and lemon juice.

title: caribbean stew
directions: Season beef and pork to taste; let stand 1 hour.
Heat oil in pot; add meats.
Brown and cook, adding hot water, for 1/2 hour. Add other ingredients and cook for another 1/2 hour.
Add Dumplings.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot with vegetables or white rice.
Serves 8.

title: cheese strata
directions: In 11 x 7-inch greased baking dish, alternate bread cubes with layers of cheese cubes.
Pour liquid mixture over this and chill at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes (uncovered).

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Wonderful on sliced ham.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt stick of butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, milk and sugar; pour in pan.
Place peaches in dish.
Add 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar to peach juice; pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese filled meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, 1 can tomato sauce, egg, bread crumbs, onion and seasonings.
Mix and divide mixture into half.
Lightly pack half into a loaf pan.
Arrange slices of cheese on mixture and cover with remaining meat.
Put rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Pour other can of tomato sauce on top and bake another 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in Pyrex dish.
Freeze.
Take out a few minutes before serving.

title: date jam
directions: Soak apricots in juice overnight.
Bring to a boil and simmer in juice until soft, or just tender.
Whiz all ingredients in blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: brown stone front cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour; add alternately with buttermilk.
Dissolve chocolate and soda in warm water.
Add to mixture.
Grease three 8-inch layer cake pans and sprinkle with flour.	Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chr-son punch(recipe originated for wedding of chris and sonja broome)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients beforehand and chill.
You can make an ice ring of these ingredients if you like, adding colorful pieces of fruit (i.e. cherries, strawberries, peach slices).
Add Sprite at time of serving.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a deep casserole dish.
Beat together 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Pour mixture over melted margarine; do not stir.
Empty cherries over flour mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Very good served with Cool Whip!

title: cape cod fish chowder
directions: Will also need 4 quart kettle.

title: sesame beef and noodles
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, cut steak lengthwise in half; thin cut crosswise into thin slices.
Cut green onion into 2-inch pieces.
Stir together beef broth, soy sauce, sesame oil and cornstarch; set aside.

title: special pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put into unbaked pastry shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Stir together milk, sugar, salt, yeast mixture, eggs, butter and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough flour to make dough smooth and easy to handle.
Knead about 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl; place greased side dough up.
Cover and raise until double.
Punch down, roll out and cover with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and let raise again.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: artichoke bites
directions: Place
the party rye out onto cookie sheet.
Brush each little bread
with
the
melted
butter.
Open artichoke can, drain and cut each artichoke into sixths.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix dressing with ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Chill.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and pour in bottom of casserole dish.
Drain green beans and pour over beef.
Pour mushroom soup over beans.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Heat in 400° oven approximately 30 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: cucumber sandwiches with mint butter
directions: Combine butter and mint.
Mix well.
Spread mint butter on bread.
Lay cucumber on 4 of the slices and top with remaining bread.
Cut them in half diagonally.
Place sandwiches on serving plate.
Add burnet sprigs and olives.
Serves 8.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook onion, celery and potatoes in chicken stock until tender. Make roux with butter and flour.
Add the milk to the vegetables and then the roux!
Keep warm on low heat or in crock-pot.

title: low calorie casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion and drain.
Stir in rice and pour over cabbage.
Pour soup over all.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: one dish supper
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add onion; cook until onion is transparent.
Add tomato sauce, water, noodles, salt, pepper, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce; boil 2 minutes.
Add olives and corn.
Turn into baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken with rice(with cling peaches)
directions: Brown chicken; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
In the chicken pan, scrape bottom of pan for chicken flavor.
Heat to boiling.
Turn into a 2-quart baking dish (casserole) lined with foil.
Add the chicken.
Close the foil on top and seal it.
Bake it about 1 hour.
Open the foil the last 10 minutes.

title: cabernet beef ragout
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and sprinkle over steak.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with Pam.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add steak and cook until browned on all sides, stirring frequently.
Transfer to 4-quart casserole.
Set aside.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels over low heat.
Add noodles and stir until coated.
Add nuts.	Drop from spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool and harden.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread dressing on bread, top with cheese, 1 Tablespoon sauerkraut and corned beef.
Spread butter on outside of each slice of bread.
Grill on both sides until brown.

title: cornbread "never fail"
directions: Beat egg with whisk.
Add milk and beat.
Add dry ingredients, stirring well.
Heat margarine in iron skillet.
Sprinkle small amount of meal in hot iron skillet, then add cornbread mixture. Bake at 475° until brown.

title: grilled sirloin & wild rice salad
directions: Preheat the grill. Prepare the rice using package directions. Cool to room temperature. Combine the lemon juice, olive oil and garlic in a small mixing bowl and mix well. Season with salt and pepper. Reserve 1/4 c. of the olive oil mixture. Sprinkle the steaks with salt and pepper. Grill over medium-hot coals for 10 minutes for medium-rare, turning and basting once with the reserved olive oil mixture. Remove to a platter. Combine the remaining olive mixture, rice and artichokes in a large mixing bowl and toss lightly. Arrange the greens on 4 dinner plates. Top the greens with a mound of the rice mixture. Cut the steak into thin strips. Fan the steak strips on top of the rice mixture. Serve immediately.

title: spanish hash
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and green peppers until meat is brown.
Stir in rice and cook 2 minutes longer.
Add broth enough to tomato juice to make 2 cups.
Stir broth mixture, tomatoes, seasonings and beans into meat.
Heat to boiling.
Stir well; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Yield:
2 (8-inch) cakes, Prep Time:
30 Minutes, Cook Time: 45 Minutes.

title: crispy oven baked chicken(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, egg white and skim milk to make a batter.
Dip chicken breasts into batter, then coat with corn flake crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour in uncovered baking dish coated with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black forest pie
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium-low heat, melt chocolate with sweetened milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in extract.
Pour into large bowl.
Cool, chill.
Thoroughly beat until smooth; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into shell.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Serve with pie filling.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine until tender.
Add mushrooms, ham and sour cream; heat until bubbly hot.

title: mom's best pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly combine pumpkin and sugar, then add spices and mix well. Stir in eggs well and then add evaporated milk and regular milk. Mix well until smooth; pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 45 minutes or until the tip of a knife inserted in the middle of the pie comes out clean.

title: homemade ice cream (in freezer)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; fold in egg whites.
Add sweet milk until 2/3 full, then add vanilla.
Stir and freeze (alternate ice and ice cream salt in freezer).

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; fill a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350°.
Bake about 30 minutes longer.
Filling will appear softer in center.

title: favorite jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over meat and marinate 6 hours or more.
Dry on racks in dehydrator or oven at 130° for about 5 hours.
Check after 2 hours.
Store in sealed container.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix fruit juice and cornstarch; cook until thick.
Place along with peaches, butter and lemon juice in casserole.
In another bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; cut in butter. Add milk and egg; mix well.
Spoon ingredients on top of fruit mixture, making a layer over all.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 400° for 25 or 35 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt in a small bowl.
Peel peaches and slice.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and almond extract; toss to coat.
Add sugar mixture; mix gently.
Put into 2 crust pie shell.
Brush top pastry with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Bake in a hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to moderate oven (350°); bake 35 minutes longer or until pastry is golden brown and juices are bubbly.
Cool.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Let jello set until thick enough to whip. Whip until fluffy, then add all the other ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream last. Set in fridge until set.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir in beef, mixing well.
On waxed paper, pat meat into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top of meat, leaving small margin around edges.
Sprinkle shredded cheese; roll and seal.
(It should look like a jelly roll, only seal the ends.)
Place open side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Place slices of Mozzarella cheese on top for last 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Pour
milk
over shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool; add yeast which has been softened in lukewarm water.	Add egg; mix well. Add
flour;
beat
well.
Let rise 2 hours or double in size, covered
and
away	from
draft.
Work
dough down.
Put dough on floured
board or table top.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Roll in rectangular strip.	This should be about 1/4 inch thickness.	Spread with
cup
melted oleo.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.	Roll.
Cut in about 1 1/2 inch rolls.
Place in greased muffin tins.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: big!!! bean pot
directions: Saute bacon and onions in large frypan.
Add garlic powder, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Combine with beans in large roaster or Dutch oven.
Add barbecue sauce and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven until bubbly and hot (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: claybourne oven pancake
directions: Heat an 8 or
10-inch cast-iron skillet in a 425° oven. Stir together milk,
eggs, salt, sugar and flour.
Melt margarine in hot skillet.
Pour	mixture
in and bake 15 minutes at 425°.
To serve,
sprinkle
powdered	sugar on top, then lemon juice.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook celery, onion and spuds well done in just enough water to keep from sticking.
Add clam juice and simmer 5 minutes.
Fry bacon until well done, but add pepper before bacon is done so flavor will blend.
Add clams and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add enough flour to thicken and simmer 10 minutes.
Put all together. Add milk and let come to a slow boil.
Season to taste.
Stir vegetables frequently to avoid sticking.
Serves 6.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix potatoes and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop large spoonfuls into well-greased skillet.
Brown both sides. Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, 1 1/2 cups of sugar, milk, butter, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Mix well.
Put fruit in a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Spoon mixture over fruit.
Mix 1 cup of sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Sprinkle this over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot cream pie
directions: Heat juice.
Pour cold water in bowl.
Sprinkle gelatine over water.
Add to hot juice.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, lemon juice and apricots, which have been put through a sieve. Cool.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk, chips and sugar to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla. Store in refrigerator up to 4 weeks, tightly covered.

title: ruby punch
directions: Chill all items, then place in a punch bowl to serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put frozen vegetables in bowl.
Add cream of celery soup and 1 soup can of milk; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Put Stove Top in a bowl; add melted butter.
Mix well.
Slice Velveeta cheese; put on top of vegetables.
Spread Stove Top mixture over Velveeta cheese; bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening in heavy skillet.
Add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions. Combine macaroni and ground beef mixture in a 2-quart baking dish. Season to taste.
Gently spoon mushroom soup into mixture.
Mix lightly, lifting from bottom.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is bubbly and browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk and add sugar and flour.
Mix and beat. Let rise.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put drained pineapple in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour and layer over pineapple.
Then layer grated cheese.
Cover with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces; salt and pepper well.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour catsup over chicken.
Arrange apricots over chicken and pour the juice over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spice raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins in 2 cups water for 10 minutes.
Save 1 cup of juice for cake.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add the rest of ingredients including reserved juice.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili con carne
directions: Place ground beef and water in pot and boil for approximately 1 1/2 hours at medium heat. Add salt, pepper and chili powder and cook at low temperature 1 hour.
Drain liquid off 1 can of beans and add to chili.
You do not have to cook any further.
Beans are not needed, but may be used, if desired.
Will serve 12 people.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Grease and flour three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Using wooden spoon
or whisk, mix sugars with butter. Mix in beaten eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust (deep-dish). Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Test with knife.

title: fudge waffles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until foamy (2 minutes).
Add buttermilk, mixing well.
Set aside.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together; seal in jar.
Mix well each time you use.
Add 2 teaspoons to each cup of hot water to make tea.

title: nancy's one dish chicken-n-gravy
directions: Dip
chicken
in
flour; place skin side down in melted butter in
a
9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Add
onions and mushrooms to chicken. Mix other ingredients
and
pour
over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Cover
with
foil
and
bake
to
20 minutes at 325°.
Serve
with
potatoes or rice.
Note:
Skinning and de-boning the chicken makes this dish fancier.

title: chocolate pie-company size
directions: Mix sugar,
flour,
salt
and
cocoa
in a bowl and set aside. Put 5
cups of milk to heat in a large saucepan.
Beat egg yolks and
add
just
a little milk to them and set aside. Pour the remaining
milk into the flour mixture and mix well. When the milk
is almost ready to boil, stir in the chocolate mixture, stirring
constantly
until it comes to a boil and is thick.
Set off burner and stir in the egg yolks.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie
shells.
This will fill 2 big and 1 small pie pans.
Top with meringue or whipped cream.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool, peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup of butter. Stir until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions and seasonings.
Fold in potatoes.
Put in 2-quart greased casserole.
Dot with remaining butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar together with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet, making a small indentation on top of each cookie.
Put a small amount of jelly in each indentation.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: onion rings
directions: Blend oil and flour.
Add milk and egg.
Beat with beater until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Dry food thoroughly, then coat with unseasoned flour.
Dip into batter, letting excess drop off.
Fry in oil 375° until golden brown.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In large container combine gelatin with boiling water, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Fold in all at once strawberries with juice, drained pineapple and nuts.
Turn half of mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish as first layer.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Evenly spread with sour cream. Gently spoon rest of strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well, reserving some juice from tomatoes to pour over loaf.
Form 2 loaves; place in baking dish or
iron skillet.
Pour remaining tomato juice over loaves.
Cook in oven at 400° until onion and pepper is done and loaves are brown on top.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Put the shortening and water together; bring to a boil, then add flour.
Put in the pie plate or pan and pat out.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
In large bowl, mix together potatoes, Crisco, sugar, salt and milk.
Cool.
To this mixture add yeast, beaten eggs and enough flour to make a medium dough. Knead slightly until smooth.
Put in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise.
(If made about 9 a.m.
the rolls can be made out at 4 p.m. for a 6 p.m. dinner.) These can be made a day or two ahead of time and refrigerated or may even be frozen for about a week.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Make sure Cool Whip, cream cheese and butter are soft.
Crush Oreos into small crumbs.
Save 2 tablespoons for top.
Mix crumbs with butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan to form the crust.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread over crust and refrigerate 20 minutes.
Mix pudding as directed for pie.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle the 2 tablespoons of crumbs over the top.
Refrigerate 6 hours!
Great!

title: brunswick stew
directions: Pressure cook and bone meat.
Cook onions and potatoes until tender.
Grind all together.
Heat, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
This makes a big pot.
(You can freeze it.)

title: spinach parmesan appetizer pie
directions: Saute onions in butter for 3 minutes; add mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in spinach, garlic, tarragon and parsley.
Simmer over medium heat, stirring constantly, until liquid evaporates. Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper; add cheese.
Combine with sauteed vegetables and pour into a lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cut into wedges and serve on individual plates with forks.
Serve hot or cold.
Can be frozen and reheated.
It pays to make 2 pies at once to use up purchased ingredients.
Serves 6 to 9.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Trim steak and cut into serving size pieces.
Place in crock-pot and cover with tomatoes.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours. May be served over rice or potatoes.
The leftovers make excellent starter stock for stew.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in a loaf pan. Top with tomato ketchup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: couscous salad
directions: Bring water or broth with salt to a boil.
Put couscous in a large bowl and pour boiled water over it.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove cover and let couscous cool enough to handle with fingers.
With fingers, crumble couscous to make it fluffy and eliminate lumps.
Let it cool completely.
In a skillet, heat 1/4 cup oil.
Saute the onion until soft and then add the curry powder.
Cook for about 2 minutes longer.
To cooled couscous, add onion, curry
mixture, chickpeas, pimiento, pepper and currants. Toss and moisten with vinegar and remaining oil.
Add salt if necessary.
This can be made up to 3 days ahead and refrigerated covered loosely with Saran Wrap.
Before serving, bring salad to room temperature and fluff it up with a fork.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Mix lime juice, cumin and garlic powder.
Set aside.
Cut chicken or turkey into thin strips.
Place meat into juice mixture and marinate for 20 minutes.
Slice green pepper and onion into thin slices.
Saute in large skillet with 2 teaspoons of oil, until tender-crisp.
Add meat mixture.
Mix well for 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with any of your favorite toppings such as cheese, lettuce, tomato or salsa.
Place on a warmed flour tortilla.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.

title: grandma dey's molasses crinkles
directions: Mix all well and put in refrigerator to chill.
Make into balls; dip in sugar and press down.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: Mix all ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to one hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Baste on and off.

title: dad's salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients, except cheese, in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in Blue cheese.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cod fish appetizer
directions: To make dressing, 1 part vinegar and 3 parts olive oil.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Melt butter over hot water in double boiler.
Add sugar and milk.
Cook over boiling water for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
Add powdered sugar until of fudge consistency.
Spread in 8-inch square pan, very lightly buttered.
Cut into squares.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in pot over medium heat. Add oysters with juice, salt and pepper. Let oysters saute in butter for a minute or two. Add evaporated milk and whole milk. Let milk come to a bubble over low to medium-low heat. Stir to prevent milk from scorching. Can add a little Tabasco sauce to kick it up. Also can add more whole milk to taste. Do not let stew boil, just come to a bubble.

title: meal in one potatoes
directions: In a medium skillet, cook ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except potatoes and cheese.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk over low heat. Watch carefully and stir often.
Mix cake mix, nuts, butter or margarine, eggs and 3 tablespoons evaporated milk or water until moistened.
Press half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Pour melted caramels over; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Top with remaining cake mixture. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Cut into squares when cool.

title: hamburger and macaroni
directions: Cook onion in butter until onion is clear. Add hamburger and brown lightly. Add tomatoes, salt, Worcestershire and Tabasco and heat to boiling. Add macaroni; cover and simmer slowly 15 to 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Take off cover and cook mixture a few more minutes to thicken slightly. Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy. Add all other ingredients with a pinch of salt.
Pour into pie shells and cook 45 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: rocky mount cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Bake three 8-inch layers.

title: ham cheese balls
directions: Mix all and shape in ball and chill (very delicious).
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Saute cabbage, celery, onion and mustard in margarine.
Add noodles, milk and corned beef.
Transfer mixture to a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: seabreeze salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O in a large bowl with electric mixer.
Add drained pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Will keep well in refrigerator.
Good with ham, chicken or pork.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add remaining ingredients except zucchini and flour.
Beat well.
Then add grated zucchini and flour.
Use 2 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
When baked, leave in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out onto rack.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Glaze with orange juice and confectioners sugar.

title: cranberry-strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries, juice and all.
Add rest of ingredients except for sour cream. Pour 1/2 of mixture in flat dish.
Place in refrigerator and let set (don't refrigerate over half of mixture).
When set, spread sour cream over mixture in dish.
Add rest of mixture and chill in refrigerator until set.

title: bean bonanza salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine drained beans.
In a blender container, place remaining ingredients.
Blend until onions and green pepper are finely chopped.
Pour salad oil mixture over beans; toss to coat.
Chill several hours, stirring occasionally. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch and 1 cup plus tablespoon sugar; add water slowly, stirring until smooth and thick.
Add egg yolks, butter, rind, juice and salt.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes over medium heat stirring. Pour in shell.
Cover with meringue made from 3 egg whites beaten stiff plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 300° until light brown.

title: better carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 300-350° for 40 minutes.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour and next four ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Heat milk and water in a heavy saucepan until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients, stirring well.
Stir in remaining 3 cups flour to form soft dough.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in warm water to cover, at least 1/2 hour. Drain and wipe dry.
Cut into quarters.
Blend and combine sugar, butter and egg.
Stir in water and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Place in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased and floured. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cold water.
Combine cranberries, sugar, orange peel, pineapple and nuts.
Let gelatin stand until slightly thickened, then add all remaining ingredients.

title: patio freeze
directions: Mix everything real good in your blender.
Pour in paper cups or ice trays and freeze.
Perfect for a hot day.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix bread, milk, beef and 1/4 cup onions together.
Shape into balls and place in baking dish.
Mix all the remaining ingredients together and pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 16 to 20 meat balls.

title: tagliarini
directions: Cook noodles 15 minutes and drain.
Cut up fine and fry onion, garlic and bell pepper.
When done, add can of tomatoes.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar and beat well. Beat Dream Whip until stiff. Add Dream Whip to cream cheese mixture. Put a layer of 1/4 of cream cheese mixture in each cooled pie shell. Then put a layer of 1/4 of blueberry filling over cream cheese mixture. Top with another layer of cream cheese mixture. Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of casserole with chicken. Mix sour cream and soup together; pour over chicken.
Cover with crushed crackers and sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Drizzle melted butter over crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 300° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with butter.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up all fruit, except bananas, and mix in a large bowl. Stir in slightly thawed orange juice.
Add banana slices just before serving.

title: california salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a pretty glass bowl for serving.
Chill well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Heat oil in cast-iron frying pan.
Add warmed oil, milk and eggs to dry ingredients.
Combine and pour into warmed cast-iron frying pan. Bake 20 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix
flour, margarine and ground nuts well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Bake
at
for	15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 8 ounce Cool Whip. Spread on baked cooled crust.
Mix milk and chocolate pudding. Spread on 2nd
layer.
Top
with 8 ounce Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.
Cut into squares.
Top each with a cherry.

title: chicken best
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Heat butter in a heavy skillet and quickly saute chicken pieces until tender.
Add pineapple chunks and green pepper.
Combine 3/4 cup pineapple juice, honey, soy sauce and cornstarch; mix until smooth.
Add to chicken mixture and cook, stirring until thickened (over medium heat).
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: chili potato stew
directions: Heat oil in large soup pot over medium heat.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring mixture to a boil.
Then cover, reduce heat to low and simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: corned beef dish
directions: In large skillet, break corned beef into pieces.
Add rice, tomatoes, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and water.
Place over high heat.
Bring to a vigorous boil.
Turn heat down.
Cover and allow to cook slowly for 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Serve from skillet if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and cook until thickened.
Put layer of vanilla wafers on bottom of bowl and around sides.
Cut bananas up on top of wafers; pour filling over bananas.
Repeat layer. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat until peaks form.
Put on top of pudding and brown in oven.

title: southern potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cooked potatoes, eggs, salt, black pepper, onion, relish, bell pepper and pimiento. Mix well. Add the mayonnaise and stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, combine first 4 ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling; boil until vinegar is reduced to 1 tablespoon.
Place double boiler top over double boiler bottom containing hot, not boiling water.
Add egg yolks; cook, beating constantly with wire whisk, until slightly thickened.
Add butter, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating constantly with whisk until butter is melted and mixture thickened.
Stir in parsley.
Serve with tenderloin.

title: chicken, chile cheese casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and shred chicken into 1-inch pieces. Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and line with tortillas.
Make a mixture of chopped onion, chilies and tomatoes, chopped chilies, sour cream, milk and cream of chicken soup.
Grate cheese.
Line pan with tortillas, chicken, soup mixture, cheese and repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken casserole #3
directions: Add 1/4 teaspoon salt to one cup of water; add chicken breasts and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove breasts and reserve 1/4 cup broth. Cut chicken into strips and place in bottom of oiled casserole. Mix sour cream and 1/4 cup chicken broth. Pour over chicken. Crush crackers and sprinkle on top. Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour on top. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Have ready a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Roll level tablespoon of the mixture into balls the size of walnuts (you should have 60) and arrange them on the pan close but not touching.
Freeze until hard, then pack in gallon size freezer storage bag.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in margarine about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, bouillon cubes and water.
Bring to boil, then simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle sliced French bread with Parmesan cheese and toast in oven.
After soup is cooked, put in individual ovenproof bowls.
Put slice of toasted bread on top, then sprinkle with grated Swiss cheese and place in oven at 425° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove when cheese is melted.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain corn, wash and drain rice. Place ingredients in layers in a 2 quart baking dish.
Pour over second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can water, cover meat with bacon.
Cover with tight fitting lid.
Bake for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Combine sugar, salt, milk and butter in a small saucepan; heat until melted.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cooled mixture; mix well.
Add flour gradually; mix thoroughly. Let dough rise in a warm place for 20 minutes. Knead down.

title: texas golden chicken
directions: First, puncture chicken with a fork and brush with orange juice.
Then spray baking pan with cooking spray.
Combine bread crumbs, salt, pepper, paprika and cayenne pepper in a plastic bag. Add chicken and shake well to coat lightly.
Lay the chicken in a single layer in the baking pan.
Bake without turning at 450° for 30 minutes or until crisp and golden brown.
Blot with a paper towel for extra crispness.
Best served at once.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon; combine with rest of ingredients.
Press into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: prunes and bacon
directions: Roll each prune with a slice of bacon and the toothpick. Bring to oven at 450° until the bacon is crispy.
Can be served as a finger food.

title: delicious roast beef
directions: Spread soup on roast; sprinkle with onion soup mix.
May put potatoes and carrots around roast about halfway through cooking. Cook at 350° for 3 hours, or until tender.

title: coconut pound cake with glaze
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and butter flavoring for 10 minutes. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to cream mixture, then milk and coconut flavoring. Fold in coconut. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice	apples;
place on bottom of greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add
water.
Mix
dry
ingredients
together	and sprinkle over
top.	Bake at 300° for 1 hour, last 15 minutes at
or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: savory squash
directions: Slice squash 3/4-inch thick; pare.
Fry bacon until crisp, then remove from pan and keep warm.
Dip squash into egg mixed with water, then into crushed corn flakes.
(Crumbs will do as well.)
Brown in hot fat; turn, season with salt and pepper and cook until tender.
Remove to a hot platter and fry the tomato slices which have been dipped in flour.
Top the squash with tomato slices and crisp bacon.
Serves 6.

title: busy day stew
directions: Place all
ingredients	in
a large covered pan (do not brown meat first).
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine pudding and milk; beat with electric mixer until well blended, about 3 minutes.
Gradually blend in chocolate until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Turn into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: First heat applesauce in saucepan, then add the 2 packages of cherry Jell-O.
Remove from stove and add the 10 ounces of 7-Up or Sprite.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: golden cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in slow cooker. pour cheese and bacon on top. Cover and cook on low 4-5 hours.

title: onion swiss dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in shallow baking dish or Pyrex bowl 15 to 20 minutes at 425° or until top is lightly browned.
Serve with pita triangles.
Cut round pita bread in 8 triangle shapes.
Split each triangle by peeling two sides apart.
Spread lightly with margarine on split side.
Lay on cookie sheet, margarine side up. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Broil approximately 3 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; dice and cook until done.
In a large mixing bowl, combine potatoes and onion.
Add salt, sugar, pepper and 2 of the eggs, diced.
Add vinegar and sour cream and mix together. Sprinkle in the mustard and stir again.
If needed, add a bit of pickle vinegar for more moisture.
Slice remaining egg and arrange over top of salad in dish from which it will be served.
Fried bacon can be crumbled over the salad.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato-tot casserole
directions: Layer bottom of pan with Tater Tots.
Fry hamburger meat in skillet.
Let meat cook until done.
Smother meat with cream of chicken soup and let simmer.
Pour hamburger meat over the bottom layer of Tater Tots.
Put shredded cheese over hamburger meat. Cover top with lined up Tater Tots.
Put in oven at about 250° or 300° and let bake until Tater Tots are brown.

title: green beans and bacon
directions: Fill 4-quart saucepan half full of water; bring to boil.
Add green beans; cook, covered 8 minutes.
Meanwhile in 12-inch skillet, cook bacon until brown.
Remove bacon to paper towels. Pour off 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Drain beans, stir in drippings in skillet.
Return bacon to skillet.
Season with salt and pepper; cook and stir over medium heat 2 minutes.
(I add chopped onion to bacon while its cooking).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together oil and seasonings.
Pour over crackers. Continue to mix until dry looking.
Great for parties and for snacks!

title: baked beans
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Mix first six ingredients together and pour into baking dish (Pyrex or Corning Ware).
Add bacon strips on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: baked cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix rice and soup together in casserole dish.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until moisture is absorbed.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix well, then add:

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: Measure dry ingredients: flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt into sifter.
Cream Crisco and sugar. Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture.
Blend well. Form teaspoons of dough into small balls, one at a time, then roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until tops are slightly rounded, crackly and light brown.
Remove to wire cake rack.
The cookie is wrinkled.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into an uncooked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Boil whole squash in salted water until almost tender.
Remove tops to make cavities for stuffing. Scoop out stringy insides and discard.
Drain water that collects.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add grated onion, cheese, bread crumbs and salt and pepper. Put bits of butter in each cavity of squash. Fill with stuffing.
Place butter and bread crumbs on top of each.
Place in a foil-lined pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken breast
directions: Place beef on bottom of greased pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of beef.
Cook bacon, cut up and combine with sour cream, soup and 1/2 can water and pour over chicken. Bake uncovered at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: fried okra
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs and milk; stir until smooth.
Add okra and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep, hot fat and fry until golden.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients for salad and keep cold until almost ready to serve.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble in salad.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, 1 1/3 cups instant potatoes (dry), egg, salt, pepper, onion, catsup and milk.
Spread in ungreased pie pan (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes.
Prepare remaining potatoes for 4 servings.
Top baked meat loaf with potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Store loosely covered up to 24 hours.

title: ritz cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on crackers.
Then put a large marshmallow on top of peanut butter.
When you have done your pan full, put in oven at 350° until marshmallows get light brown. Remove from oven and they are ready to eat.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Crush together wafers, 1/2 cup peanuts and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: frozen pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together well; add pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts (save a few nuts for the top).
Mix well.
Fill pie shells and freeze.
Pies will keep for 2 months in freezer.

title: smoked sausage jambalaya
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. While rice is cooking, coat inside of a large skillet with Pam cooking spray according to directions. Heat skillet over medium heat.
Add sausage, onion, green pepper and celery. Saute until vegetables are tender. Add tomatoes, hot pepper sauce and pepper.
Drain cooked rice and stir into sausage mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until thoroughly heated.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13 pan.
Layer potatoes.
Cover with chopped onion and shredded cabbage.
Crumble corned beef over this.
Mix cream of celery soup with milk.
Pour over the layers. Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a small bowl, melt the butter.
White it's hot, add both sugars.
Stir, then let cool a bit.
While the butter mixture is cooling, mix the flour, soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
In a small bowl, beat the egg lightly with a fork, then add the egg and vanilla to the butter mixture.
Stir.
Now, add the butter, egg and vanilla to the flour mixture in the mixing bowl.
Stir again, then add chocolate chips and nuts, if you want them.
Stir everything until it's all mixed up well and put the bowl in the refrigerator to cool for about an hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and black pepper in large bowl.
Toss steak slices in mixture to coat.
Heat margarine in heavy skillet over moderate high heat until bubbly.
Add 1/2 steak slices; cook, stirring once or twice, until no pink remains.
Remove; repeat with remaining steak.
Reduce heat to moderate low.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add mushrooms, beef broth and tomato paste.
Raise to high heat and cook for 2 minutes, scraping up brown bits stuck to skillet.
Return steak and accumulated juice to skillet; heat through.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Cut and cream together flour, sugar, salt and Crisco until crumbly.
In separate bowl mix together cold water, vinegar and egg. Pour this mixture over flour mixture. This will moisten dry flour mixture.
Make into 5 equal balls to roll into pie crusts. Roll thin.
Will keep in freezer for weeks.
Yields 1 single, 2 double crusts.

title: aunt polly's squash casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick chili
directions: Lightly brown meat and onion.
Add the beans, bell pepper, seasonings and tomatoes. Simmer approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Measure
popped
corn
into
buttered bowl (4 quarts or larger).
Combine
together
in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan the sugar,
water,
corn
syrup, salt and vinegar.
Stir over heat until
sugar
is dissolved.
Cover, bring to boil and let boil briskly
for 3 minutes.
Uncover, insert candy thermometer and cook
mixture to hard ball stage, 260°.
(I cook it until when you drip
a
little in a cup of ice water, it stays in a very hard ball.)
Remove
from heat.
Stir in vanilla and coloring (if wanted).
Pour
slowly
over popped corn, stirring with a large buttered
spoon
to
coat all corn.
Form into balls at once with buttered hands, handle gently to avoid packing.

title: pineapple-cheese stuffed celery
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Chill for 2 or more hours. Serve.

title: banana bran bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray a 8 x 8 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. In a medium bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and cereal. Mix well. In a small bowl, combine milk, egg substitute, carrot, banana, and walnuts. Combine milk mixture and dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into prepared baking dish. Bake for 25-35 minutes or until lightly browned. Cut into 6 bars.

title: crab-stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Slice stem end from tomatoes; scoop out pulp.
Combine crab meat, green onions, parsley flakes, vinegar, bread crumbs and dill weed in bowl; mix well.
Stuff tomatoes with crab meat mixture. Arrange on paper towel-lined plate.
Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes or until heated through, turning plate once or twice. Garnish with paprika.
Makes 5 servings.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Fill cooked shell with the cheeses; set aside.
Mix together cream, chives, onion, curry powder, salt and pepper in a 4 cup measure or 1-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High (100%) for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until steaming.
Stir a small enough amount of hot cream into eggs; stir egg mixture into the remaining hot cream. Pour in shell.
Sprinkle with ham.
Microwave for 12 to 14 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Turn dish a half turn halfway through cooking.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles. Place triangles with points toward middle of a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with hash browns and Cheddar.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan (if desired) and bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: real chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter or margarine and brown sugar. Blend in eggs, salt, soda and vanilla. Mix in flour, then chips. Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, maybe less depending on your oven, or until lightly browned. Cool slightly. Remove from sheet.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Cut each chicken wing at joints to make 3 pieces; discard tips.
Place chicken in ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken. Cover and refrigerate, turning chicken occasionally, at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drain chicken; reserve marinade. Place chicken on rack in aluminum foil lined broiler pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Brush with reserved marinade.
Turn chicken; bake brushing occasionally with marinade until tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: beef patties with potatoes and onions
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, milk, chopped onion, salt and black pepper. Shape into 10 to 12 small patties. Coat with flour.
Heat oil in large skillet. Saute onion slices until tender but not browned. Remove onions. Add beef patties to skillet and brown on both sides.
Cover with sliced potatoes and sauteed onions. Sprinkle with salt and black pepper, to taste.
Add boiling water and cover tightly.
Cook over low to medium low heat until potatoes are tender.
This usually takes about 10 to 15 minutes, according to thickness of potato slices.

title: christmas lime jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Whip cream and add sugar after it starts to thicken.
Mix softened cheese, pineapple, nuts and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add to jello.
Set until firm.
Looks beautiful in individual or large mold.

title: butter icing
directions: Mix everything together.
Let it come to a hard boil for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Set it off the stove for 15 minutes.
Beat it real hard until it is ready to spread on cake.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast and 1/4 cup water until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, egg and liquid or melted shortening.
Mix well with whisk. Add 1 1/4 cups warm water; mix well.
Add enough flour until mixture can be handled.
Grease top.
Cover with cloth and let rise until doubles in size.
Make into rolls or loaves.
Let rise again until it doubles.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Will make 2 large loaves or 18 rolls.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix jello
with
hot water and stir well.
Add cake mix and stir well.	Add eggs and oil; beat on low speed until well blended.
Then beat for 5 minutes at high speed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve plain or with powdered sugar glaze.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8-inch square pan.
Blend the remaining ingredients until crumbling; spread over the apples. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Preheat oven 325° - greased 13 x 9 baking dish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges together.
Add sugar and let stand about 1 hour.
Chop celery fine.
Dissolve jello in hot water; stir until dissolved good.
Let cool awhile and add to cranberries.
Stir occasionally until begins to jell.
Real tasty.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Drain.
Cut pepper and onion fine. Boil
together
until
tender.
Drain.
Add
pimento, mayonnaise, cheese and soup.
Pour mixed ingredients in 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and butter for 15 minutes to cream mixture. Layer into graham cracker crust the mixture, pineapple, mixture, bananas, mixture, Cool Whip, cherries and chocolate to decorate.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Pour cherries in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries.
Do not stir.
Pour oleo over cake mix and sprinkle nuts on top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Delicious topped with ice cream.

title: shrimp dish
directions: Boil shrimp in salt water and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add flour to make a paste; add cheese sauce and thyme, salt, garlic powder, and pepper to taste.
Add shrimp to mixture; serve over rice.

title: eggs ala goldenrod
directions: Make paste out of butter and flour.
Warm milk and stir in butter and flour mix.
Heat and stir until smooth and thick (medium sauce).
Chop eggs and add to sauce, leaving a couple of yolks to scatter on top of dish for garnish.
Spoon egg sauce over slices of toast.

title: scones
directions: Heat milk and shortening.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat eggs; add to warm milk.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add liquid after some of the flour.
Let rise.
Do not knead first time up. Keep dough soft.
Roll out and cut into squares.
Deep fry until golden.

title: mary's pork chops
directions: Slightly brown pork chops in a skillet. Place in a Pyrex dish. Slice potatoes and onions and place over chops. Add soup and water. Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: squash pie
directions: Blend well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fried rice
directions: In large frying pan, fry bacon until almost crisp.
Soak up excess fat with paper towels, leaving some fat.
Add vegetables and stir-fry for a minute or two, then add rice.
Fry the beaten eggs in a pan coated with Pam.
Thinly pour the egg mixture into pan.
