Turn over being careful not to let it burn.
Keep doing this until all egg mixture has been cooked.
Place on a cutting board. Cut each into 3 to 4 strips and then several times crosswise.
Mix with the rice, salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Pour over batter. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together.
In casserole put Velveeta, oregano, garlic salt, soy or Worcestershire sauce and meat mixture.
Mix. Microwave for 2 minutes or until cheese melts. Spread on Pepperidge Farm or cream bread.

title: chess pie
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well and turn into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until set.

title: peanut butter roll(non-cooked type)
directions: Mix sugar, oleo,
about
1 tablespoon milk and vanilla. Add a little more
milk
until
consistency
is like a pliable dough. Roll out
onto
wax
paper	sprinkled
generously with powdered sugar until it
is about 1/8 inch thick.
Then spread with peanut butter and roll up.
Store in wax paper, then wrap with foil, put in	refrigerator
and
slice
when you want it. Will keep for a couple of weeks in refrigerator.

title: stove-top baked beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings. Add beans, molasses and mustard. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler for two
directions: In a small pan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and water until smooth. Add peaches and bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Reduce heat to low; stir in butter and lemon juice.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Allow the cheese and sausage to soften some. Mix all ingredients (by hand). Divide into several large balls and continue to knead each ball until everything is thoroughly mixed. Form small balls (2-inches) from each of the large balls. Arrange on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes (until balls are brown and sizzling). Makes approximately 100 sausage/cheese balls.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel pears before grinding.
Mix ingredients in order given and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pack into jars and seal at once.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: Blend all ingredients at low speed in blender or food processor until thoroughly mixed.
Bottle with a tight cover. Refrigerate overnight, at least, to blend flavors.
Then keep in refrigerator.
Shake before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.
Will keep for a month.

title: strawberry slushies
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil just until sugar is dissolved. Mix all ingredients together and put in freezer.
Halfway through freezing process, stir entire mixture to give slushy effect. Fresh strawberries can be substituted (about 1 quart).
Refreshing summer drink.

title: "one of a kind" potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Do not overcook!
Cool.
In large bowl, mix rest of ingredients.
Add diced potatoes and fold in. Serves 8 to 12.

title: cucumber bean boats
directions: Combine beans, pepper and onions.
Peel cucumbers and cut lengthwise.
Scoop out seed.
Fill cucumbers with bean mixture and serve on crisp lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients together, then add nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until light brown.
This recipe makes 5 loaf pans; when pouring, divide into pan evenly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly mix brown sugar, salt, flour and spice.
Add slightly beaten eggs and pumpkin.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in milk.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 minutes longer or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: fudgy sherbet pie
directions: Brush 9-inch pie pan with oil.
In large bowl, combine cereal, nuts and frosting.
Blend until cereal is well coated.
Press on bottom and up sides of pan.
Freeze about 30 minutes or until firm. Spoon into crust evenly, then top evenly with vanilla ice cream. Freeze.
Serve with Cool Whip and chopped nuts for garnish.

title: red velvet cake 1(aunt brenda's favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Cream together oil and sugar; add eggs.
Blend well.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
In separate bowl, dissolve baking soda in vinegar; add to original batter.
Mix in flour, small portions at a time. Add food coloring last.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake starts to brown.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Do not cook rice, soak for small amount of time.
Take large leaves of cabbage and wilt them in warm water.
Make balls with rice and meat; wrap cabbage leaves around them.
Cook slow in tomato sauce for 2 hours or cook in presto cooker.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Combine remaining ingredients and add together; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful into greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Brown onion in butter; add mushrooms, mushroom soup, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Stir until smooth; cover and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add evaporated milk. Add olives, shrimp and tuna.
Stir.
Do not boil.

title: five flavored pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar until light.
Add flavorings.
Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into floured and greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender in small amount of boiling, salted water.
Saute celery and onion until tender.
Add drained eggplant to celery mixture.
Saute lightly.
Remove from heat and add egg and milk.
Pour in 1-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat, add pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto buttered cookie sheets.
Chill.
Melt paraffin and morsels (or bark chocolate) in a heavy saucepan over low heat. Dip candy into chocolate and return to cookie sheets.

title: calico beans by linda and chuck
directions: Fry ground beef and drain.
Fry bacon and drain.
In 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole, add meat, beans, sugar, onion, catsup and anything else you want to add.
Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
After baking, stir once before serving.

title: real german sauerkraut
directions: Start with 1 to 2 cups water and 6 to 10 cups naturally fermented sauerkraut, without chemical preservatives.
Low-salt is best if you can get it.
In a large pot, place the kraut, water and about 1 to 2 pounds of leftover roast (anything).
Remove skin and/or fat.
Add some defatted roast drippings or low-fat gravy or your favorite natural gravy mix.
Simmer, covered, for about 1 1/2 to 3 hours.
This can easily make a full dinner, combined with a nice potato dish.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Place margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in a saucepan; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients quickly and blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and chill.

title: beef and peppers
directions: Saute garlic in shortening.
Add meat.
Brown well over high heat, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle in salt and sugar.
Add mushrooms.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender. Stir in green pepper and gravy.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan, mixing well.
Heat until warm; do not boil.
Spoon a small amount of sauce into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Fill tortillas with chicken, sauce and cheese.
Roll up to enclose filling.
Arrange in prepared dish. Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (I add 2 tablespoons of picante sauce to soup mixture.)

title: the original chex party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Melt butter in large roasting pan in oven. Stir in seasonings. Gradually stir in remaining ingredients until evenly coated. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towel to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: pier four marinated mushrooms
directions: Place all ingredients, except mushrooms, in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Place mushrooms in bowl and coat well.
Let stand 20 minutes and stir again.
Place mushrooms and liquid in 3 large glass jars (mayonnaise jars).
Marinate 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.
Shake daily.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Gradually stir in milk, a little at a time.
Stir constantly until smooth.
When mixture begins to thicken, stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir a small amount of mixture into egg yolks.
Put egg yolks into chocolate mixture and continue stirring for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend flour, margarine and salt until looks like meal.
Press with spoon into an 8-inch square pan over the bottom and half up the sides.
Arrange peaches on crust and sprinkle with the sifted cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 20 minutes. Mix reserved juice, milk and egg; pour over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes or until custard is firm, except in center.
Will become firm on standing a while.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Put all in blender and mix for a minute or two.
Use romaine and croutons.

title: fig and strawberry jam
directions: Mix well and boil 3 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with noodles.

title: rancho sausage supper
directions: In a large skillet, fry sausage until pink color disappears; drain. Add onions and green pepper; cook slowly for 10 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, sour cream, macaroni, chili powder, salt and sugar. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently, until macaroni is done. Serve hot with a green salad and hard rolls.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and form into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter, add cocoa and mix.
Add rest of ingredients. Beat with mixer until thick and creamy.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and pie cherries.
Cook, stirring until mixture thickens and boils.
Stir in butter and extract, if used.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie pan. Cover with top crust.
Seal the edges.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix lightly the cooked macaroni, cheese, cracker crumbs and milk. Add salt and pepper to taste. Top with butter. Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and powdered sugar together 3 times; set aside. Place egg whites, cream of tartar and salt in large bowl; beat until foamy.
Gradually add granulated sugar (about 2 tablespoons at a time).
Continue beating until meringue holds stiff peaks. Fold in vanilla and extract.
Gradually add flour to egg whites; fold in gently just until flour disappears.
Spoon batter into ungreased tube pan.
Gently cut through batter with knife.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn upside down on a funnel; cool 30 minutes.
A 2-piece tube cake pan is best to use.

title: horseradish pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oil in frying pan or Dutch oven.
Pour off drippings.
Season meat with salt and pepper.
Add tomato juice, onion and horseradish.
Cover and cook slowly 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.
Remove roast.
Combine flour and water and add to cooking liquid.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy; add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's, raisins and nuts. Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes before removing cookie.

title: maple walnut salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place salmon fillet (skin side down) in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
In small bowl, combine maple syrup and walnuts.
Spread over top of salmon. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes with fork and the color is light pink.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours.
The longer you simmer, the better it is.
If too thick, add water.
Serve over cooked pasta with garlic bread.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix jello and water; cool and thicken.
Beat cheese spread and mayonnaise; add jello and cream.
Add remaining ingredients. Grease mold with a little mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.

title: philadelphia cream cheese spread
directions: Beat and cook egg yolks, sugar, vinegar and water until thick. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, pimiento and onion together, then add to egg mixture and beat until smooth.

title: royal salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add sugar, pineapple juice and salt. Chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients. Makes 6 molds.

title: mock greek salad
directions: Break lettuce in bite-size chunks.
Add cheese, olives, pimientos and anchovies.
In jar, combine oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic for dressing.
Shake well.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss lightly.
Serves 10.

title: sparerib marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
To speed up cooking time, precook ribs. Boil for 15 minutes first.
Pour marinade in gallon Ziploc bag and add ribs.
Turn a few times.
Best to marinade overnight.
Grill on low an hour, basting often.

title: hot crab meat souffle
directions: Put 6 slices of bread, diced, in a long baking dish.
Mix crab meat, mayonnaise, onion, green pepper, celery and cheese and spread over bread.
Trim crusts from remaining 6 slices of bread and place over crab meat mixture.
Mix eggs, milk and vermouth and pour over mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Take out 2 1/2 hours before serving.
Bake 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Remove from oven; spread mushroom soup over top and bake 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate delight and icing
directions: Mix well.
Beat
about	2 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in 1/2 of butter.
Set aside.
Add remaining butter to same pan and saute chicken sprinkled with Beau Monde until brown on all sides.
Add wine, mushrooms and tarragon. Simmer 45 minutes until tender.
Place chicken on platter and keep warm.
Deglaze pan with sour cream.
Pour sauce over chicken. Garnish with green onions.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: three layer keebler bars
directions: Line a 9 x 12-inch pan
with whole crackers.
Melt margarine and add both sugars, milk and crushed crackers.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers in pan.
Place another layer of whole crackers on boiled mixture and press down gently.
Melt butterscotch, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over last layer of crackers.
Set and store in refrigerator.

title: potato salad
directions: Lightly toss first 4
ingredients
together
in a bowl. Fry bacon in skillet until
browned.
Stir
a
mixture
of the next 4 ingredients into vinegar
and water.
Add to the beaten eggs and mix well.
Pour
egg
mixture
into hot bacon and fat and stir until mixture
thickens, about 10 minutes.
Pour over potato mixture and toss
lightly.
Chill
several hours before serving.

title: lemon chicken wings
directions: Shake chicken, flour,
salt
and pepper in plastic bag. Arrange in single layer
in
baking pan.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400°.
Flip chicken over.
Mix lemon juice, soy
sauce,
oil
and garlic.	Pour over chicken. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Flip chicken and bake 1/2 hour more at 350°.

title: oven fried vegetables
directions: Spray cold baking sheet with nonstick coating.
In pie plate, stir together first three ingredients.
In medium bowl, place vegetables.
Drizzle vegetables with salad dressing.
Toss to coat. Roll vegetables in crumb mixture to coat.
Place in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden. Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: six week raisin bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, beat oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Add baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add Raisin Bran; mix thoroughly.
Store batter in covered container in refrigerator for up to six weeks.
Bake as many as you want at a time.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tin. Fill muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Large muffins, 25 minutes.

title: lazy stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook rice in 4 cups water; stir-fry hamburg with onions, then add 1 can tomato sauce.
Add salt and pepper; add rice.
Take middle of cabbage out with a knife.
Take leaves apart one by one; cook in water until soft.
Spread cabbage in a 9 x 13-inch pan. For one layer, add half of hamburg mix, cover with another layer of cabbage, then rest of hamburg mix.
Cover with rest of cabbage. Put bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: piccata di petto di tacchino
directions: Pound turkey slices gently.
Dust with flour, patting it on to make sure it sticks.
Melt the butter and oil; saute turkey slices in the butter mixture, turning them when the edges get white (about 3 minutes).
Remove to warm platter.
Add wine and lemon juice to mixture;
salt to taste.
Simmer meat for about 2 minutes.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Season and put on low flame.
Cut cheese in cubes and add to meat.
Stir until melted.
Put on party rye and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
These can also be frozen ahead of time.

title: chili
directions: Chop onion and green pepper and saute in oil.
Add tomato puree, tomato paste and water.
Simmer.
Add hamburger; cook about one hour or more.
Add chili beans, kidney beans, chili powder and crushed red pepper, if desired.
Simmer for 40 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream together. Spread on top of cooled crust.

title: chicken salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Line platter with lettuce leaves.
Place chicken salad in center of platter.
Place pear halves around edges of platter.

title: basic preserves(any fruit)
directions: Stir well cold.
Cook in heavy pot briskly and stir with wooden spoon.
After juice clarifies, when it will web on silver fork, take off heat.
Let stand for 15 to 30 minutes.
Bottle. Seal with paraffin.
Makes 3 to 4 standard 1/4 pint jars.

title: d. a.'s best spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic in a large stockpot in a tablespoon of olive oil.
When meat is almost cooked, add mushrooms and onions; continue browning until vegetables are slightly tender. Drain meat mixture.
Add oregano, basil, thyme, bay leaves and tomatoes.
Bring almost to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Add tomato paste, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Continue simmering for 1 more hour.
Serve over your favorite pasta.
Recipe makes approximately 1 gallon of sauce.
Freezes in Ziploc bags well for another day.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Mix cream cheese with chili peppers until spreadable.
Spread thin layer on tortilla shell and roll up flat.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Dip into salsa.

title: cheri's jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into glass bowl.
Let sit. Spread sour cream on top of jello.
Add rest of mixture on top. Chill.

title: messy mississippi mud pie
directions: Chop and crush Oreo cookies; save some for the top. Melt butter in a bowl in the microwave. Pour melted butter over crushed cookies. Stir and put in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Pat cookie crumbs down with the back of a spoon. Put the pan into the freezer while mixing the pudding according to directions on package. Take pan from the freezer and put a layer of Cool Whip on top of the cold cookie crumbs. Put back into freezer. When pudding thickens, pour pudding over top of the layer of Cool Whip. Top pudding with Cool Whip again and sprinkle remainder of crumbs and your favorite candies on top.

title: best french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend for 3 minutes. Mixture will be thick.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine cream of wheat, flour, salt, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add Crisco; mix well.
Add enough buttermilk to make a thin-like mixture.
Pour into a skillet or baking pan which has been greased with cold Crisco, sides and bottom and dusted with the dry mixture.
Have pan or skillet cold when you grease it.
Place in hot oven and bake at 475° for 15 to 20 minutes or when you think it is done.
The bread will come out of pan or skillet as soon as you take it out of oven.
It looks like and tastes like corn bread, only better, I think.

title: chicketti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Put everything in casserole except save 1/2 of the cheese for top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Whip chilled milk and add to thickened jello mix.
Add bits of cream cheese, nuts and mayonnaise.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter, stir in ground beef, flour, salt and pepper. Saute for 5 minutes. Add soup, mushrooms and catsup. Simmer for 20-30 minutes. Stir in sour cream when ready to serve. Serve over noodles. I like to use rice too.

title: one crust rhubarb pie
directions: Line a pie pan with unbaked crust.
Dice washed rhubarb and pile it rather high in pie shell.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, 2 egg yolks, 4 tablespoons melted butter and 4 tablespoons flour.
Pour custard on top of rhubarb.
Bake slowly.
Make a meringue of the egg whites or you may serve the pie plain or with whipped cream.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread, spread lightly with butter.
Arrange 6 slices bread, buttered side up, in greased rectangular 3-quart baking dish.
Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Drain.
Layer half the sausage and cheese over the bread.
Add remaining bread, sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs with milk in bowl. Pour over casserole, press until milk saturates all layers. Chill overnight.

title: one bowl plain cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together into a large bowl.
Add shortening, vanilla and 2/3 cup milk.
Beat 2 minutes on slow speed of electric mixer.
Add 1/3 cup milk and eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake in two 9-inch well-greased cake pans.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour.
Add butter and mix thoroughly.
(If dough seems dry, work with hands.)
Mold 1 teaspoon dough around each olive; shape into ball.
Place 2 inches apart in ungreased baking sheet.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pat's meat loaf
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Place in roasting pan.
Shape meat loaf into loaf style; cover with 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Chop onion into medium pieces.
Slice the smoked sausage into 1 inch pieces.
Place the chopped onion, and washed beans into a slow cooker early in the day to allow enough time to cook properly. Cover these ingredients with water and simmer on high.
After about 2 hours of simmering add the smoked sausage into the beans.
Lower the heat setting to medium and simmer for 2 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: Cut top off bread.
Scoop out the bread; set aside, leaving shell.
Mix thoroughly all the other ingredients and pour into shell.
Cut the set aside bread into easy to handle pieces for dipping.
When the bread chunks are all gone, don't be surprised to find your guests tearing the shell apart and dipping that too! It's that good.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs; salt and pepper to taste.
Brown sausage; cook and crumble bacon.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Crumble bread in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour melted butter over bread.
Layer sausage, onion and pepper.
Pour eggs over layers.
Spread cheese to cover, then top with crumbled bacon.
Bake slow for 1 hour or until cheese has slightly browned.
(Best when made the night before and refrigerated.)

title: german winter carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain.
Slice carrots.
Combine with mayonnaise, parsley, salt and pepper in a serving bowl.
Mix well.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Saute onion in bacon drippings; stir in sugar and vinegar.
Add to carrot mixture; mix well. Sprinkle with bacon.
Serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broiled fish fillets
directions: Put the fillets, skin side down, on a greased broiler pan. Mix the butter and lemon juice and brush over the fillets (sparingly).
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Put under the broiler so the fillets are 4-inches from heat.
Cook 10 minutes for each inch of thickness.
Serve at once.

title: caesar salad
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp.
Pour the bacon fat into a bowl and add the bread cubes.
Add the salt, pepper, oregano, basil, mustard and thyme and toss until the cubes are completely coated.
Place the cubes on a cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven until they are golden brown, stirring occasionally to ensure that they don't burn.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Mix the taco mix and beans; spread on a large platter, then spread the avocado dip over it, then spread on the chili, olives, taco sauces, topped with the green onions, and last put the 2 cheeses on top.

title: vegetable-barley soup
directions: Cover the chuck roast with water and add the next 9 ingredients.
Simmer until the meat is tender.
Take out the meat and strain the stock.
Let stock cool in refrigerator until fat comes to top.
Cut up celery, onions and carrots.
Add barley, tomatoes or juice to taste.
Add all of these ingredients to soup stock.
Simmer until the vegetables are tender.
Cut up the meat in small pieces and add to the simmering soup.
Turn off heat.
Let sit and flavor through.
Adjust seasoning as desired.
Serve with love and pride.
Good luck!

title: dip for fruit
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy. Add other ingredients, mixing until light and fluffy. Serve with fresh fruit. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: beef stew
directions: Trim any excess fat from the meat.
Combine flour and seasonings.
Coat the meat with flour.
Brown in hot oil in heavy kettle.
Sprinkle any remaining flour over meat.
Combine tomato paste and beef broth, then pour over meat.
Braise onions and vegetables in oil.
Cook slowly until golden.
Add vegetables to meat mixture.
Cover and cook slowly until the meat is tender, about 2 or 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Cream together brown and white sugar and butter.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and add to peanut butter mixture a little at a time.
Then add milk.
Drop mixture onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
Put Hershey Kiss in the middle of cookie as soon as cookies come out of oven.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Pour over meat and cheese.
Cover with Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: liver and onions
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove; crumble and set aside.
Add onions to bacon drippings; cook slowly until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Cook liver with seasoned flour.
Saute liver quickly in same skillet over high heat (do not overcook).
When liver is still pink in center, add wine vinegar (this helps blend all flavors and helps remove all brown bits from pan).
Remove to platter and top with crumbled bacon and onion rings (spoon wine vinegar glaze over each serving of liver) optional.

title: pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/8 cup warm water.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups warm water, brown sugar and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Heat oven to 475°.
Place twisted pretzel on cookie sheet.
Brush beaten egg on top of pretzel, then sprinkle pretzel salt on top.
Place cookie sheet in oven.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until pretzel is pale golden brown or until done.

title: peggy's fried okra
directions: Wash okra.
Leave small pods whole.
Cut large pods into 12-inch slices.
Beat egg and milk together.
Add salt and pepper. Pour mixture over okra.
Shake gently into a bag containing cornmeal.
Fry slices in hot fat until golden brown (4 to 7 minutes).

title: potato torte
directions: You will need a tube pan.

title: apple butterscotch dip
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk, chips and salt.
Heat on low heat.
Cook until melted and creamy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cinnamon and vinegar.
Serve with apple wedges for dipping or other fruits of your choice.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Can serve over ice cream.

title: russian salad
directions: Shred lettuce in a bowl, arrange remaining ingredients on top. Serve with French dressing.

title: sunday morning quiche
directions: Cook pie crust	at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix everything and pour into pie
crust.
Cook
at
350° for 30 minutes.
Let quiche "rest" for	5
minutes
after
removing from oven so it will be firm and easy to cut.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked deep dish pie shells.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into plastic jugs.
Put into freezer until icy.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: hamburg patties
directions: In a large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 can of soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
Shape firmly into 6 patties.

title: caramel marshmallow popcorn
directions: Melt butter, marshmallows and brown sugar.
Pour over popped corn, stir and let set.

title: chilaquiles
directions: Cut tortillas in pieces.
Fry in a skillet until golden.
In another skillet fry tomato sauce in 1/2 teaspoon oil.
Add salt, garlic powder and crushed pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Cool slightly; add sour cream.
In a casserole dish spread some tortillas; follow with tomato sauce, cheese, chicken breast and onion.
Proceed until done.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: venison lo mein
directions: Slice slightly frozen steak into strips cut diagonally. Combine water, soy sauce, bouillon granules and cornstarch in small bowl.
Set aside.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Cook the eggs in a house on the stove; cook for 45 minutes on medium heat.

title: scalloped potatoes with parsley(amounts are for 4 servings.)
directions: Arrange half the potatoes in a well buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with half the onion and half the parsley.
Arrange remaining potato, onion and parsley as a second layer.

title: german style potato salad
directions: Boil peeled potatoes until cooked.
Dice onion and green pepper.
Cut bacon in small pieces and cook until brown.
Add vinegar and sugar to bacon after it is brown.
Bring mixture to a boil. Dice potatoes into cubes.
Add chopped onions and green pepper. Add all ingredients in bowl and mix. Allow to set at room temperature for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serve still warm. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: one minute fudge icing
directions: Combine all except vanilla.
Bring to a boil; let boil hard for 1 minute.
Cool a little; add vanilla and beat until smooth. So good.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Separate and flatten rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: citrus marmalade
directions: Wash fruit.
Cut
in
half lengthwise and cut into very thin slices crosswise.
Remove
all
seeds.
Place
fruits
in large bowl.
Add
water.
Let soak overnight.
Place water and fruit in large saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook until tender. Add sugar and stir
well.
Bring
to
boil and boil rapidly to jell stage (220° on
candy thermometer) from 15 to 30 minutes. Quickly skim off any
foam
and
ladle into sterilized jars to 1/8-inch from the top.
Seal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix whole kernel corn, creamed corn, cheese, egg and 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers and 1/2 stick margarine.
Cook in microwave for 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients, then chill.
Eat (without guilt!). Modify recipe, as desired, by using a variety of pasta and/or vegetables.
Other options can include:
1/2 cup grated carrots, green or red onions and Parmesan cheese.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple; bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Save some pecans to put on top of salad.
Let set until firm.

title: robby's dip
directions: Fry ground beef until brown, drain grease off and set aside. Put milk and cheese in a heavy saucepan. Melt, mix in slowly ground beef, salsa, and refried beans. Keep warm when serving.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread meat in a layer on bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with frozen Tater Tots.
Pour soup over potatoes and cover with cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carolyn's crabmeat pie
directions: Mix mayonnaise, flour, eggs, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add crabmeat, cheese and onions.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Add onion and carrot.
Stir in broccoli.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Stir in milk; let thicken (about 10 minutes on medium-high temperature).
Add cheese; let melt.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
(Don't let soup boil; just keep warm on low heat.

title: dion's dirty rice
directions: Brown ground beef in large pan with 1 cup water and sesame oil.
DO NOT DRAIN.
Add two cups of water to sauce pan and bring to boil.
Work ground beef so it is not clumping together.	Add rice mix with curry powder and return to boil.
Stir to mix ingredients.
(You can add regular rice and extra water to increase yield.) Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 - 25 minutes.
Add mushrooms and soy sauce while stirring.
Remove pan from heat and let stand for 5 minutes to complete absorption of water.
Fluff with large fork before serving.
Serve with cool side dishes such as salad and chilled avocado.
Consider a tart desert such as lemon pie.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and eggs.
Add flour, milk, sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add butter.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in pan of hot water in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese, flour, salt, and pepper.
Dip chicken in milk and egg mixture.
Coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour or until chicken is tender.

title: great sweet potatoes
directions: In microwave safe dish, place sweet potatoes, butter or margarine and brown sugar.
Microwave for about 6 to 8 minutes, cover with a lid.
When all has melted, stir in 1/2 cup Eagle Brand milk.
Very tasty.

title: carolyn's tacoritos
directions: Brown meat and drain; add chili powder, garlic powder and onion.
Combine 2 cups white sauce (canned or homemade), sage, oregano, salt, cumin and green chilies.
Reserve 1 cup white sauce and 1 cup grated cheese.
Mix remaining sauce and cheese with meat, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and butter together and press in pie pan. Place in refrigerator or you could use graham cracker crust.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice, cream cheese and vanilla.
Beat well and spoon on pie crust.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Let mixture boil well, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Mix well.
Add cornflakes and mix well.
Work quickly, putting mixture into greased pan.
Press down and cut in squares while still warm.
Makes 72 portions.
Half recipe works for family size.

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Mix for about 2 minutes, then let set about 3 hours or overnight. Put in small glass jars and freeze.

title: light king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in a large skillet coated with Pam over medium-high heat 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in chicken and next 6 ingredients; remove from heat. Tear tortillas into 1-inch pieces; layer 1/3 pieces in bottom of 13 x 9 baking pan coated with Pam. Top with 1/3 chicken mixture and 1/3 cheese. Repeat layers twice. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chilled tomato soup with mint
directions: Core the tomatoes and
cut them into eighths.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and
add
the onion, garlic and allspice. Cook briefly
and
add
the flour, stirring.
Add the tomatoes and broth and
stir constantly.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Bring to the
boil
and
let
simmer about 20 minutes.
Strain through a food
mill.
Let
cook;
chill thoroughly.
Put the soup in a mixing
bowl and add the sour cream, stirring with a wire whisk. To	blend:	Before serving add the mint.
Garnish if desired, with sour cream.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer the ingredients in the order listed.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: diet smucker's chicken salad with wild rice
directions: Heat chicken over medium-high heat until hot and cook each side for about 2 minutes or until brown. Put chicken in 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until cooked through. Then cool and cut into 1/4-inch strips. In large bowl, combine the chicken, rice, green onions, grapes and pecans. Toss well and set aside. In small bowl, combine orange rind and next 4 ingredients. Stir well. Pour over the mixture. Toss well. Serve. Makes 7 servings.

title: omi's german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes to done.
Peel while still hot and cut into thin slices.
Mix together oil, vinegar, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and parsley.
Beat to a thick sauce.
Pour the sauce over the potatoes and mix gently so potatoes are not mashed.
After mixing, cool overnight.

title: tropical chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine pineapple, lime juice and cloves.
Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Add to marinade. Cover and refrigerate for at least 45 minutes.
Drain, reserving marinade.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put the
fruit	in
bottom of an 8 or 9 x 12-inch dish. Arrange bread
cubes
on top of fruit.
Beat together the egg, sugar,
flour
and melted margarine.
Pour over bread, soaking each piece.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: minestrone
directions: Rinse Great Northern beans.
In a large kettle or Dutch oven, combine beans and 4 cups water. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
(Or, cover and soak in the water overnight.)
Do not drain. Add beef broth. Return to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

Stir in cabbage, potatoes, carrots, zucchini, onion, undrained tomatoes, green beans, garlic, salt and basil. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 35 to 45 minutes or just until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 main dish or 12 side dish servings.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In a large stockpot, bring chicken stock to a boil.
Reduce heat to moderate and add chicken.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix flour and margarine, then press into a 13 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken tenders casserole
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole with chicken strips.
Place cheese slices over the chicken.
Mix soup and wine then pour over chicken and cheese.
Crush the stuffing mix and sprinkle over the top.
Drizzle melted margarine over the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soup mix(dry)
directions: Makes a nice gift.
Put in Ziploc bag and add cooking instructions.
Makes dry bean mix.

title: hangover soup
directions: Heat tomato juice and baking soda to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add milk and oleo.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef, drain off grease.
Mix beef, tomato paste, tomato sauce, green peppers and onion together.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with cheddar and mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy skillet paella
directions: In large, deep skillet, cook sausage and chicken wings in fat from sausage over high heat.
Cook about 10 minutes, adding oil if necessary.
Remove to bowl.
To drippings in skillet, add onion, bell pepper, turmeric and cayenne pepper; cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: jelly roll cake
directions: Bake quickly; spread with jelly and roll as soon as taken from the oven.

title: baloni
directions: Mix hamburger and Tender Quick together.
Set in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Divide into 4 balls and roll into logs.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets in 250° oven for 2 hours (turn every 1/2 hour).

title: slaw
directions: Grate cabbage with carrots and onion, toss in salad oil and refrigerate.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, celery seed, sugar, mustard and salt.
Mix in cabbage and refrigerate several hours, if possible.

title: insect repellant
directions: Drink before going outside to keep insects and ticks off.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Blend ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour mix over a roasting pan full of popcorn.
Stir until covered.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour and stir while baking every 15 minutes.

title: broccoli dip(servings:  8)
directions: Cook broccoli in unsalted water until tender.
Drain.
Melt margarine; add chopped onion, mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Stir and mix until mixture can be poured easily.
Arrange in casserole in alternate layers: broccoli, sliced cheese and sauce.
Save some cheese for top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve as a dip with chips or as a casserole.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix and bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: miracle salad
directions: Mix vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients together, pour over vegetables and toss.
Refrigerate 2 hours and serve.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Put sugar, vinegar, oil, ketchup and salt in a pint jar; shake until all the sugar is dissolved.
Pour over salad and serve immediately.
Any variety of fresh vegetables can be used.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and Mandarin oranges together.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350°.
Cool completely.
Mix together Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and vanilla pudding; spread over cake.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all but last three ingredients well.
Put in baking dish and cover with almonds, cornflakes and dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, lightly spray muffin tins with cooking spray.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese, egg, 1/3 c. sugar and 1/8 tsp. salt until light and fluffy.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Cook to a hard ball stage, 250°.
Beat egg whites; add vanilla and add syrup mixture when done.
Beat with Mixmaster until it sets up.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: no set jello
directions: Empty cottage cheese into bowl and stir dry jello into it. Add Cool Whip and stir; add pineapple and stir.
Add mandarin oranges and carefully fold so you don't break the mandarin orange pieces.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: puddin' cake
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Hershey's syrup.
Set aside.
Bake cake according to directions on the box, using 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
While still warm, take handle of a wooden spoon and poke holes in top of cake (the more the merrier).
Pour chocolate mixture over the top of the cake.
Cool completely!
Frost with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in a buttered baking dish.
Add minced onions; sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Dot with butter.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Pour hot milk over all and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix
2 cups Bisquick, sugar, egg and milk.
Beat vigorously. Spread
in
greased round pan (9 x 1 1/2-inches).
Mix 1/3
cup Bisquick,
brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle
over cake.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: home-style applesauce
directions: In slow cooking pot, combine apples and water.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Add sugar and cook on low another 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon at serving time.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Use an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix egg, flour, sugar, baking soda and fruit cocktail.
Pour into square pan.
Sprinkle light brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve in squares with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: horseradish bloody mary
directions: In large pitcher, combine tomato juice, vodka, lemon juice, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce and salt.
Chill several hours or overnight.
At serving time, pour over ice.
Use celery stick stirrer in each glass.
Makes 2 quarts.
(I use little or no salt.)

title: cauliflower and cheese(microwave)
directions: Place cauliflower in a dish and cover.
Cook on High 5 minutes per pound.
Turn a quarter-turn halfway through.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix Miracle Whip, salt and mustard in a 2-cup measure.
Cook mixture 1 minute on High.
Stir well.
Frost cauliflower, top with cheese.
Cook, uncovered, on High 1 minute. Serve.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables by directions on package.
Drain when done. Add next 4 ingredients and put in casserole. Top with 1 stack pack broken Ritz crackers.
Melt 1 stick oleo and drizzle over crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs and mix well.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla, add sifted flour, salt and soda; mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen. Bake at 375° for 12 to 25 minutes.

title: savory spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion, pepper, garlic and celery in butter until vegetables are tender.
Add soups, water, spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
In 3-quart casserole, alternate spaghetti, sauce and cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling and hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: whipped cream filling
directions: Beat whipping cream and vanilla until foamy. Gradually add powdered sugar and beat until soft peaks form.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 2/3 cup sugar into egg yolks.
Place in saucepan.
Add salt; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until milk is scalded.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Combine 6 tablespoons sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to egg whites gradually, beating to soft peaks.
Fold into milk mixture; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Chill for 3 to 5 days to develop flavor.
Pour into punch bowl and dot with whipped cream.

title: dede's caramel nut slices
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour and soda.
Blend in nuts.
Form into two rolls, 2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight. Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot).
Cut in slices about 1/8-inch thick.
Place a little apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen cookies.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Remove from bones and add back to stock along with onion, pepper, celery and tomatoes.
Add water, if necessary, and cook until onion, pepper and celery are tender.
Add spaghetti and cook until spaghetti is done.
There should not be any liquid left.
When spaghetti is done, add Velveeta cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Don't let spaghetti cook out too dry.
If this happens, add a small amount of canned chicken broth.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
In a saucepan melt butter, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
In another bowl, mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to above mixture and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured shallow pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Start making the icing the last five minutes the cake is baking.

title: rosemary bread
directions: Place yeast, sugar and water in large bowl and allow mixture to bubble.
Mix in 2 cups flour and the salt.
Add 1 tablespoon of freshly chopped rosemary.
Knead for about 10 minutes by hand until smooth and elastic.
Add additional flour, if necessary. Oil a bowl, put dough in it and cover with a towel.
Let rise in warm place for 1 hour until doubled.
Punch down and divide in half. Let dough rest 5 to 10 minutes.
Spray baking pan and shape dough into 2 small rounded, oval loaves.
Melt butter and brush over the top of each loaf.
Sprinkle remaining tablespoon of rosemary over the loaves and press lightly into surface.
Let rise again until doubled.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Let bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: plum cake
directions: Put in tube pan and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: apple crumble
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Grease a 2-pint dish; fill with sliced apples, layered with sugar to taste (add cinnamon and/or raisins, if desired).
Rub butter into flour until mixture resembles breadcrumbs; add sugar and mix.
Sprinkle crumble thickly over fruit; press down lightly.
Put into preheated 375° oven and bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake about 45 minutes more, until top is light brown.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: soup-er chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cool.
Bone and cube.
Combine with soups in bowl.
Add bread and mix well.
Stir in eggs.
Spoon in to lightly greased 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit concentrate
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large gallon jug or jar.
Store in refrigerator.
Use 1 cup of mix to 3 cups of water.
Children love this one!

title: 5 day sweet pickles
directions: Pour boiling water over cucumbers for 3 mornings. On the 4th morning, drain good and bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, salt and pickling spice. Pour over cucumbers; let set overnight. Bring to boil next morning and pack in jars. Pour syrup over and seal. Does not need water bath.

title: italian chicken
directions: Heat skillet to 350°.
Season pieces of chicken with salt and pepper, then brown in oil.
Add onion, garlic and cooking sauce. Cover and reduce to low heat.
Simmer.
Cook until meat is tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti or over cooked rice. Serves 4 or more.

title: hot feta artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spoon into a 9-inch pie plate or 3-cup shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with Stoned Wheat Thins crackers. Makes 2 cups.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Cut slices of bacon just long enough to encircle and overlap water chestnuts.
Secure the bacon with a toothpick.
Place in a bowl of soy sauce for several hours.
Remove from sauce and broil until crisp.
Makes 32 servings.

title: dilly dip
directions: Combine all ingredients well and chill.
Serve as dip with cucumbers, carrot sticks, radishes, green pepper, green onion, cherry tomatoes, cauliflower, celery, etc.

title: bavarian brownies
directions: In a large bowl combine cake mix, milk, butter and egg.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Spread batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: *Do not use Peter Pan peanut butter; too oily.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and hot water and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: salsa slaw
directions: Cook corn in microwave for 2 minutes.
Set aside to cool. While corn is cooking, shred onion.

title: pea, cheese and dill salad
directions: Rinse frozen peas in cold water to separate; drain.
Toss all ingredients.
Line bowl with lettuce leaves and fill with pea salad.
Great for potluck!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Pour over margarine, then pour peaches over.
Do not stir. Bake at 325° until done.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together and form into 60 small meatballs.
Brown lightly in a small amount of hot fat.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form a roll (mix with hands). Coat with crumbs.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight. Slice and serve.

title: coffee cake
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in dish and set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Put butter or margarine in mixing bowl.
Mix to soften.
Add sugar and mix together.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix together sour cream and baking soda.
First, add some flour mixture to mixing bowl, then sour cream, until they are all used up.
Pour half of batter into tube pan and sprinkle with nut mixture.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle with the rest of nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine or butter in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over, then pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order listed. Press down slightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or lightly browned. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: ground beef 'n pepper
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion until onion is tender.
Drain excess fat.
Season with pepper. Stir in gravy. Add green pepper. Simmer, uncovered, until pepper is just tender, stirring occasionally. Serve over noodles.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: drop ginger cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water to cover for 10 minutes, then drain. Sift soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves with flour.
Cream lard and add sugar, eggs, flour mixture and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven (350°).
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: mainstay chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bring chicken, milk, sour cream and soup to boiling.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Beat remainder until almost smooth and pour over the chicken.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice and hamburger pie
directions: Combine sauce, crumbs, hamburger, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl and mix well.
Pat the meat mixture into the bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Combine rice, sauce, salt and cheese.
Spoon rice mixture into meat mixture.
Cover with foil. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Uncover.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy one pot meals
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frypan in hot oil and drain. Add tomato soup.

title: surprise pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg and beat.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, alternating with milk and flavoring.
Pour into a fairly deep pan or casserole dish.
Over this, sprinkle brown sugar (free from lumps), then pour on cream. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
The dough rises to the top and the cream and sugar make a delicious caramel sauce.
Cool slightly; serve warm upside down.

title: dressing
directions: Break and dry bread crumbs in a large bowl. In a separate pan, saut onions and celery until tender. Add to bread crumbs. Also add sage, salt and Accent. Pour broth over bread crumb mixture. Stir well and let cool. When cooled, add eggs. Beat well. Make sure dressing is a little soupy. Add oysters last if desired. Add enough seasonings to suit your taste. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13 greased pan.

title: my mom's cranberry sauce
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar, water and apple in a large pot and boil gently until all berries pop, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Mix well.
When cool, add celery and pecans.
Refrigerate.
Freezes well.
Makes a half gallon.

title: aunt maggie's elderberry syrup
directions: Gather ripe elderberries.
Cover with water and stew well. To every pint of the juice, add one pound sugar, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Boil for 1/2 hour and bottle when cool.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together refried beans, taco seasoning and water.
Spread in bottom of pan.
On top spread sour cream, then chilies, onion, tomato and Cheddar cheese, layered.
I usually double everything, except sour cream and seasoning.
Use seasoning to taste.
Chill. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cappuccino shake
directions: In a blender, combine milk, coffee crystals, sugar and extract.
Blend until coffee is dissolved.
Serve with a dash of cinnamon.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar, salt, butter and raisins.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Keep watch and stir often.
Add vanilla and nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Brown your ground beef and chopped onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add your tomato soup to meat mixture.
Boil your macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir until all noodles are stirred in.
Put into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Lay your sliced cheese on top to cover and bake at 350° until cheese is brown and bubbly.

title: asparagus souffle
directions: Beat eggs in blender.
Add the rest of ingredients, one at a time.
Pour
into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Put dish in pan of	water.	Bake
at
350°	for
1	hour or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix well. Let set couple hours. Serve with chips or Tostitos. Good in Fritos or Tostitos Scoops.

title: 3 day chocolate coconut cake
directions: Thaw coconut; set aside.
Prepare cake as directed on box; make 2 layers.
Split layers horizontally after cooling.
Blend together sugar, coconut and sour cream.
Chill in refrigerator. Spread all but one cup of the mixture between the 4 layers.
Blend the remaining cup of mixture with Cool Whip and spread on top and side of cake.
Refrigerate for 3 days.
Refrigerate after cutting.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix together and press into an aluminum foil-lined 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: zenobia bryant's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs
with
sugar.
Add
Karo, beating thoroughly. Beat with electric mixer.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.	Add 1 cup pecans, then
stir.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Bake about 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Spoon ice cream evenly over bottom of pie shell. Store in freezer while preparing pumpkin mixture.

title: garlic dills
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Pack head of dill, clove of garlic, pickles, clove of garlic, head of dill.
Pour spice mix over pickles.
Lid and cool.
Let set 6 to 8 weeks before opening.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Make batter of flour, sugar and milk.
Melt butter in dish or pan (approximately 12 x 7-inch).
Pour in batter.
Add fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potatoes italian
directions: Partially boil potatoes with skins.
When cool, cut into quarters.
Place on a cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle dressing over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Potatoes should be nicely browned.
Serves 4.
Each serving contains 88 calories, 2.3 g protein, 0 fat, 0 chol. and 67 mg sodium.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown hamburger and saut onions. Cook spaghetti according to box directions. Cube cheese and add to hot hamburger. Stir until melted. Add seasonings and onions and mix well. Drain spaghetti and stir in sauce. In large container, combine the meat and spaghetti mixtures. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Top with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can be frozen.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add vanilla and water.
Add flour; mix well and add pecans.
Form into crescent shapes and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until delicately brown.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: never fail icing
directions: Boil cream of tartar, sugar and hot water until it spins a thread about 10 inches long.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff; add 2 tablespoons cold water and then add sugar.
Pour syrup into egg white mixture and beat until it begins to grain or get stiff, then spread on cake.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs; add melted margarine, sugar, lemon juice and lemon flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: pink paradise puff
directions: Dissolve jello in water; stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken.
Fold in cool whip. Layer a 9 inch pan with cake; pour half of strawberry mixture on top; repeat layers.
Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine both kinds of cheese.
Mix milk and butter.
Now add salt, pepper, onion salt and garlic salt to cooked macaroni.
Toss all ingredients until well blended. Place in a greased casserole; cover with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 5 to 7 minutes longer.

title: toll house pie
directions: Melt and cool butter.
Beat eggs; add flour and sugar.
Heat 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes at 325°.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, milk and egg yolks and cook over low heat or use double boiler until thick.
Stir in lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Cool the custard slightly; fill the pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Line a 9 inch square pan with crescent roll dough.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Set aside.

title: recipe for friendship
directions: Mix ingredients together for as long as possible!
Serve to everyone you know and top with much prayer.

title: diet napoleon squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine; spread in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool. Mix packages of pudding (dry), pineapple with juice, lemon juice and Cool Whip; spread over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken; tear into pieces.
Cook broccoli and drain.
In small pot, combine cheese, butter, soup and chicken broth.
Heat on stove until cheese melts.
Line bottom of casserole dish with cracker crumbs.
Layer broccoli and chicken; layer over and over, then pour cheese sauce over it.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Enjoy!

title: barbecued beef
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Brown meat in oil over medium heat.
Transfer meat to casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and cook in 325° oven until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bean soup
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain and rinse. In a large pot, cover beans with fresh water; add other ingredients, cover pot and cook 3 to 4 hours, until beans are done.
Serve with cornbread.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: stewed potatoes
directions: In large pot, cover potatoes with water and cook until done. Drain 3/4 c. of the water. Add butter, onion, salt and pepper. Cook slowly until soup thickens. Great with almost any meat.

title: oreo cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar; set aside.
Mix in large bowl until thick, 3 cups milk, pudding mixes and vanilla.
Mix both mixtures together with Cool Whip. Crumble 1/2 of cookies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over cookies.
Crumble other 1/2 of cookies over this and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: market cheese cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar together.
Add cream cheese, vanilla and flour.
Mix for at least 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours, mixing occasionally.
Good cold or room temperature.
Serves 12.

title: alaskan sourdough starter and bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water in large glass or ceramic bowl. Stir in flour and sugar, beating until smooth.
Let stand in warm place (85°) for about 36 hours, stirring occasionally.
Stir well just before using.
Pour out the amount of starter needed. Replenish remaining starter by adding 1 cup each flour and water, beating well.
Let stand in warm place until bubbly.
Place in covered jar and refrigerate for future use.

title: tommy's easy egg and sausage puff
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Cook 1 hour.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the hamburger, cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.

Layer in Pyrex oblong dish, sauce mix, lasagna noodles (uncooked), sauce mix, Parmesan cheese, noodles, sauce mix and top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (45 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered). Can be frozen uncooked.
Just add 15 minutes to covered cooking time.

title: swedish pie
directions: Beat egg and sugar, add rest of ingredients.
Bake in an 8-inch pie pan at 350° approximately 25 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with Eagle Brand sweet milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly in buttered 8 or 9-inch pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Store loosely at room temperature.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: french meatballs
directions: Mix well, form 1-inch balls and bake at 450° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Stir in eggs, buttermilk and shortening; beat until smooth.

title: snack mix
directions: Slightly break up pretzels and add remaining ingredients. Place in sealed container.

title: greek lemon soup
directions: Heat chicken stock in saucepan.
Add rice, cover and simmer until rice is cooked.
In a bowl, beat eggs and lemon juice together.
Add 1/2 cup hot stock, one tablespoon at a time, to the egg and lemon mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into chicken stock.

title: cool rise white bread
directions: Day 1:
The day you receive your starter, do nothing.

title: golden potatoes casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skin.
Chill.
Then peel and grate in large bowl.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, combine butter and cheese, stirring occasionally, until almost melted.
Remove from heat.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, Crisco and eggs.
Mix on low speed of mixer.
Add alternately the flour and milk on low speed.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Add flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes on high. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in a cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, then at 350° for an additional 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: liver in wine sauce
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan.
While oil is heating, cut the liver into thin strips and dredge in the flour.
(Put flour in a plastic bag and shake the liver strips in the flour.) Saute the onions in the heated oil until almost transparent.
Add the floured liver and fry.
Stir constantly.
This easily burns.
When the liver has lost all signs of the white flour, pour in wine.
Stir gently to mix liver, onions and flour on bottom of pan and wine.
Reduce the heat to medium-low and cover pan.
Wine and liver will cook nicely in 20 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Grease and flour two pie pans.
Beat eggs well, add sugar, flour and milk.
Add vanilla and melted butter.
Stir in coconut and divide mixture in 2 pie pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: roman eggplant
directions: Dip eggplant in butter, then in mixture of bread crumbs and salt.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Spoon sauce on top of each slice; sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Serves 5.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour, lemon extract and buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar, add eggs one at at time and sift together dry ingredients. Add gradually while beating.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes, or until cake tests done. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix well flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and sugar and then add Wesson oil, eggs, vanilla, apples and nuts.
Mix well and pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: praline cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease and flour a 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: maggie's "delectable" pecan pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large mixing bowl until well blended and smooth.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 55 minutes or until a toothpick is inserted halfway between the center and edge comes out clean with nothing stuck to the toothpick.
Cool for 15 to 20 minutes and then, wow! Serve.
Excellent with vanilla ice cream.

title: punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea; let stand 5 minutes.
Strain and add sugar, cold water and juices.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until hard ball stage (254°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Slowly pour syrup over large bowl of popcorn.
Toss until coated.
With buttered fingers, quickly shape into 16 balls.

title: microwave peanut brittle(easy)
directions: Butter a cookie sheet.
Put first 4 ingredients in microwave at Full power for 5 minutes.
(I cook mine 3 minutes, stir and cook 2 more.)
Cook 3 minutes more for a total of 8 minutes cooking time. Add butter and vanilla; cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from oven and add soda; stir quickly.
Be ready to pour in a hurry.
Spread out as thin as possible.

title: tex-mex cornbread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients. Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread in layers in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
First the pineapple, second the pie filling, third the dry cake mix, fourth the pecans and last, cut up the butter and place over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: layered beef-potato casserole(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground chuck into 2-quart glass casserole.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap, turning back one section to vent steam. Microwave at High setting for 5 minutes or until meat loses its pink color, stirring after 3 minutes.
Pour off excess fat.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add caraway seed and raisins.
Mix together butter, egg and buttermilk.
Stir into flour mixture.
(Mixture will be thick and lumpy.)
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cucumber deviled ham round sandwiches
directions: Cut bread slices into circles with 2-inch biscuit cutter. Spread each thinly with softened butter or margarine; place an 1/8-inch slice of cucumber on each.
Combine remaining ingredients except parsley and put 1/2 teaspoon of mixture on top of each cucumber slice.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Makes 68 round sandwiches.
"This is good to serve for something special!"

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons of cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: applesauce donuts
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients.
Stir baking soda into applesauce (make sure your bowl is about a 1-quart size).
Beat eggs well. Gradually add sugars and oil, beating well.
Beat in applesauce and vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternating with milk, mixing well.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil (375°).
Turn when half done. Drain on paper towel. Roll in sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain off water and add 1/2 stick of butter and the cheese.
Stir and pour into casserole.
Crush crackers and melt 1/2 butter and mix and pour on top of broccoli.
Brown in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and blend well.

Add beaten eggs. Heat applesauce to beyond warm but not to piping hot. Add baking soda to applesauce and stir until foaming. Add to other ingredients. Rub raisins with a little flour and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.
Can be served as is or with confectioners sugar icing.

title: creamed asparagus
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Drain liquid from asparagus and add enough milk to make 2 cups.
Stir liquid into paste.
Cook slowly.

title: quick caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Put 16 cups popped corn in large grocery sack.
Combine brown sugar, light Karo syrup, butter and salt; stir in well vanilla and baking soda.
Pour into bag over popcorn.
Shake.
Microwave 30 seconds.
Shake; microwave 30 seconds.
Pour out on foil and cool.

title: helen's strawberry sherbet
directions: Beat with mixer a full 20 minutes in large bowl.
It will expand and be fluffy.
Pour into 1 large container or several small ones.
Freeze.

title: lemon lust
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: enchiladas dos
directions: Cook beef and onions until meat is browned and onions are tender.
Drain.
Stir in salt.
Divide meat onto tortillas.
Top each with 1 to 2 tablespoons taco sauce and 1 tablespoon cheese. Roll up; place, seam side down, in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or an 8 x 8-inch dish.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour and chicken bouillon.
Stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chili peppers.
Gradually stir half of the mixture into sour cream.
Return to remaining mixture in saucepan. Pour over tortillas in baking dish.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In cake pan, layer Doritos (crushed), chicken leg parts (cooked and shredded) 2 cans each of cream of chicken soup and stewed tomatoes (already combined and heated) and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serve topped with sour cream.

title: sugar-free lemon chess pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Bring water to a boil, add gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Add milk to pudding mix and blend as to package directions.
Add dissolved gelatin and cream cheese to pudding mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: finger jello(won't melt!  great to take anywhere.)
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put the ingredients in the order given, adding boiling water last.
Stir until everything is well mixed. Refrigerate overnight, then cut into 1-inch cubes.
Leave plain or lightly roll in powdered sugar.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread rolls out on jelly roll pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes (not brown).
Cool 10 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix altogether, except for potato chips.
Put into buttered casserole.
Top with the crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Plump raisins (cover with water and bring to a boil).
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes before draining.
Dissolve sugar in liquids before adding dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes,
water, onion, sweet pepper, bouillon and pepper in a
quart crockery cooker.
Cover; cook on low heat setting for 4 to
1/2 hours or until potatoes are very tender. Stir in
sausage,
cheese
and
milk.
Cover; cook on medium heat setting for 30 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch and add water slowly, stirring constantly.
Boil over low heat until thickened (about 5 minutes). Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, then 1 egg may be beaten in.
Yields 1 cup.

title: pecan roll
directions: Roll graham crackers until finely crushed.* Add raisins and pecans.
Stir in milk.
Pack firm into a roll.
Add chopped candied cherries if you prefer.
Chill and slice.

title: crock-pot pork dish
directions: Put
into crock-pot.
Stir together.
Cover and cook on high for
hour,
then on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Batter should be smooth and not too thin.
Heat about 1-inch of oil in electric skillet to 375° or on stove top on medium-high.
Pour about 1/4 to 1/3 cup batter into a medium size funnel.
Hold over skillet and release batter, moving in a circular motion.
Make a complete ring, closing ends of batter together.
Continue pouring batter inside ring to make any design, making sure to connect batter to the outside ring.
Brown each side for about 1 minute, using tongs to turn.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Best when eaten warm!

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: For shortcake, add 1/2 cup sugar.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans and onions.
Drain.
Mix in other vegetables, soup and cheese.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cover with fried onions and bake an additional 10 minutes or until brown.

title: pork roast with vegetables
directions: Grease baking dish; layer sliced potatoes, then sliced onions, then sauerkraut.
Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper. Coat with mustard.
Place roast on kraut.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done.

title: salmon rice loaf(microwaved)
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients (salmon juice, not salmon) in casserole (microwave-safe) and microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir after 1 minute.
Add salmon, broccoli and rice to casserole. Mix well.
Cover (vented).
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Stir at 2 and 6 minutes.
Serves 6.
Serve with a salad.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: caesar salad
directions: Blend garlic, salt, black pepper and anchovy paste into a paste.
Blend mustard into paste.
