Blend Worcestershire sauce into paste.
Blend vinegar into paste.
Blend vegetable oil in increments of 2 tablespoons (up to 8 tablespoons, depending on salad size) into paste.
Squeeze 1 slice of lemon into paste. Blend.
Crack the coddled egg (see note) into paste.
Whip until smooth.
Dump cool, crisp, slightly damp lettuce into bowl.
Pour on dressing.
Toss.
Add croutons and Parmesan cheese.
Toss.

title: "the frogs" steak marinade
directions: Combine the soy sauce, onions and garlic in blender at high speed until very smooth. Stir in other 3 items. Makes 2 1/2 cups marinade and will keep for weeks.

title: instant banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding mix and milk according to package directions.
Fold in sour cream and 1/2 the Cool Whip.
Layer crackers, bananas and pudding until all are used.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: banana fritters
directions: Mix well, then cut 3 bananas (not overripe) into pieces and dip
in
batter.
Fry in deep fat, drain on paper towels. Can be sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Serve hot or cold.

title: lamb casserole
directions: In skillet, brown lamb and garlic. Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered. Place noodles in greased 13 x 9 dish. Top with tomato sauce mixture. Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Stir in onion. Spread over meat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Take out and sprinkle Cheddar cheese and paprika. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Serve.

title: applesauce stack cake
directions: Sift flour, then mix sugar with flour.
Melt margarine and beat eggs.
Add margarine, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk to flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Grease and flour pans.
Make five layers. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until done.
When cooled, spread applesauce with sugar between layers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jell according to box, except 1/2 cup less of cold water.
Wash cranberries and put in blender along with apples. Add a little jell liquid to help chop.
Put in bowl and add sugar and mix; when dissolved, add gelatin mixture.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Salt water to taste and put to boil with brisket and soup bone.
Let boil 1 hour. Add all vegetables. Cook until tender. Add additional water to maintain the amount wanted.
Cook vermicelli for the last 16 minutes of cooking. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: autumn pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, beating slightly.
Bake at 325°.

title: grated potato casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in order given in a blender.
Blend only until the potatoes are grated.
Do not overblend! Pour into prepared 8 x 8-inch or 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with pepper rings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop carrots and celery; cook in boiling water about 10 minutes, until tender.
Chop onion.
Cook in butter until tender. Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly; stir until smooth.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese, vegetables and cooking liquid; stir over low heat until cheese melts.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Set in your freezer.
Stir every few hours until it becomes slushy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and add to salad; mix.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream in large bowl shortening or margarine, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add egg, milk and vanilla to the creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients slowly.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape by rounded teaspoon into balls.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and press one kiss in the center of each cookie until cookie cracks around edge.
Return to oven and bake 2 more minutes.
Remove, cool and enjoy!

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
To toast slivered almonds, saute in a small amount of butter until they start to brown.
Sprinkle on crab dip.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Using Crisco, brown pork chops in skillet.
Then layer in the crock-pot and pour soup and onion over.
Do not add water to the soup.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer in just enough water to cover chicken, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Cool and debone chicken; spread buns in pan. Pour juice over buns.
Mix other ingredients and pour over buns. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvres
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze water from the spinach but not completely dry.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread on flour tortilla and roll it up, jelly roll style.
Roll, then wrap in Saran Wrap.
Chill overnight.
Cut roll into 1 inch serving sizes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown
sausage in frying pan and spread in baking dish. Pour rice over sausage.	Then pour tomato juice over rice and sausage and bake until rice is done.
Serve hot.

title: chicken with brandied mushroom sauce
directions: In large skillet, heat oil; add chicken.
Cook, turning once, until browned on both sides and juices run clear when pierced with fork.
Transfer chicken to serving platter; keep warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box; drain.
Melt butter or margarine in dish.
Combine ingredients.
Top with Ritz crackers (crumbled).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove
from
broth
and pull from bone,
tearing into small
pieces.
Place
chicken
into bottom of baking dish in a single
layer.
Combine
soup
and broth together; thicken enough to form gravy-like consistency. Pour across layered chicken and top
with
biscuits.
Bake
at 350° to 400° until biscuits are good and brown.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cocktail sauce. Mold into a ball. Put in refrigerator and refrigerate for at least 4 hours. When ready to serve, put cocktail sauce on ball.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine soup, pepper, dry rice and onion.
Melt margarine and use part to grease baking dish.
Put rice mixture into baking dish.
Salt and pepper chicken and place on top of rice mixture. Pour remainder of margarine over chicken.
Bake uncovered in the oven at 270° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: quick fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat.
Stir in sugar and milk.
Cook until thickened and sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla. Can be thinned if too thick by adding more milk.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a skillet and saute onion, bell pepper, celery, garlic and ham for 10 minutes.
Cut the eggplants into quarters and boil for 30 minutes.
Scoop out the pulp and blend it well with the sauteed mixture.
Fold in cracker crumbs, cheese (reserving a little cracker crumbs and cheese for the top) and crabmeat.
Add salt and pepper to taste and fill the eggplant shells with mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and crumbs.
Bake until brown.
Serves 8.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Slice oranges and lemon.
Combine all ingredients in large pan.
Simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Strain cider. Serve warm.

title: ezekiel bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine water, honey, olive oil and yeast.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Mix all beans, millet, wheat, flour, barley and lentils.
Grind in a flour mill. Add milled flour and salt to yeast mixture.
Stir until well mixed, about 10 minutes.
Dough will be like a batter bread.
Pour dough into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Let dough rise in a warm place about 1 hour.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until loaves are golden brown.

title: hawaiian hot bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add shortening.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture and blend.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Stir just enough to combine.
Pour batter into greased 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Before slicing, be sure and let loaf completely cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: stir-fried rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of oil and stir-fry ham, mushrooms, peas and carrots for about 2 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Heat another 3 tablespoons of oil and stir-fry scallions and rice.
Add salt and soy sauce while stir-frying.
When rice is thoroughly heated, push rice to side of skillet.
Pour 2 tablespoons oil in center of skillet.
Scramble eggs in oil until cooked, then mix eggs into rice mixture.
Return previously cooked vegetables to skillet until rice is fairly dry.

title: diet steak and vegetables
directions: Cut steak into 4 pieces.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Roll in flour.
Heat oil in skillet.
Place steak in oil and brown on both sides.
Add vegetables and water and simmer until meat is tender. Serves 4. Has 181 calories, 8 fat grams; food exchanges equal 3 meat, 1/2 fat, 1 vegetable.

title: mother's coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in top of double boiler. Beat egg yolks in small bowl and add 1/4 cup of milk. Heat 1 3/4 cups milk and add to sugar and flour mixture. Cook in double boiler, stirring until it thickens. Slowly add eggs and milk to mixture, stirring constantly. Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly. Add coconut and pour into pastry shell. Make meringue by beating egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff. Add sugar gradually and continue beating until it holds a peak. Spread on pie and bake at 400° until brown.

title: date nut bread
directions: Raisins can be substituted for dates.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits in the milk, water and salt.
Add garlic cheese and oleo; cook gently until cheese is melted.
Beat egg yolks and blend in hot grits mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in. Pour into greased casserole and bake at 375° until brown, about 25 minutes.
Great with all meals!

title: strawberry sin
directions: Beat egg whites in a small, chilled bowl until stiff and glossy.
Whip 2 cups cream with sugar in medium bowl until stiff. Whisk strawberry puree into cream until mixture is very thick. Gently fold in egg whites, blending well.
Spoon into small dessert bowls.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Garnish each with whipped cream just before serving.

title: sheryls clam batter
directions: Mix eggs and milk together.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs until moist and smooth.
Stir chocolate chips into mixture.
Pour dough into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
Make sure cake does not turn too brown, just light golden brown.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Form patties.
Place in hot oil in a frying pan.
Brown on both sides.

title: tequila dip
directions: Mash avocados.
Add lime juice; set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in tequila, hot sauce, salt and pepper. Stir in avocado; set aside.
Rub rim of serving bowl with lime wedge. Put salt on a plate.
Dip rim of bowl in salt, coating well. Spoon dip into bowl.
Yields 3 cups.
Serve with chips.

title: talorini
directions: Sear ground round until brown, breaking into pieces.
Add tomatoes (undrained), tomato paste and noodles.
When noodles are tender, add corn and cubed cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake in greased casserole dish, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Best refrigerated overnight and baked the next day.
Twenty minutes before cooking time is up, sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese sprinkled with paprika.
Will feed 20.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Crumble graham crackers; mix with 2 tablespoons sugar. Melt butter; mix with graham crackers and sugar.
Spread and flatten in spring-form pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool while mixing other ingredients.

title: queen anne cake
directions: Cook cake (according to directions on box) in 3 layers.

title: ryan's lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker pie shells.
Chill and serve.

title: aunt mary's spoon burgers (sloppy joes)
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, bell pepper and celery.
Drain. Add all remaining ingredients and simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: zucchini squash cake
directions: Grease and flour large rectangle cake pan.
Mix squash, sugar, oil and eggs together.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix with squash mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. May also be cooked in tube pan.

title: herbed pork and apples
directions: Combine herbs, salt and pepper; rub over roast.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain fat.
Mix apples and onion with brown sugar; spoon around roast.
Continue to roast 1 hour or until internal temperature reaches 160° to 170°.
Transfer the roast, apples and onion to a serving platter and keep warm.
Skim excess fat from meat juices; pour into a heavy skillet (or leave in the roasting pan if it can be heated on stovetop).
Add apple juice and syrup.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until liquid has been reduced by half, about 1 cup.
Slice roast and serve with gravy. Yields about 12 servings.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables in large bowl; stir together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill overnight. This keeps about a week or 10 days in refrigerator.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: red ketchup
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients for 1 1/4 hours.
After you cook it, add the sugar and tomato paste.

title: nutmeg sauce
directions: Combine sugar, nutmeg and cornstarch.
Pour in boiling water. Add orange peel and boil 10 minutes.
Add brandy and reheat.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Put the oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat and sear the roast in the oil until it's dark brown all over. Remove the roast from the Dutch oven. Put 1/4 cup of the water and the sliced onions in the Dutch oven and place the roast directly on top of the onions. Cover the Dutch oven; set the burner to low and forget about it for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: In large saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Add marshmallows; cook and stir until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal.
Using wax paper, press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: quick fudge
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 8-inch dish and set aside.
Sift cocoa and sugar.
Slice butter onto cocoa mixture.
Pour on evaporated milk.
Cook in microwave 2 minutes on High (maybe 30 seconds longer).
Pour into mixing bowl and add vanilla and nuts; stir. Pour in greased dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Combine ingredients and mix well. Chill about 1 hour before serving.
Serve with veggies and/or bread chunks.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring chicken, water, onions, pepper, salt and celery to a boil.
Simmer for 2 hours, or until tender.
Take chicken out; cool and pick off.
Put broth through colander; return broth to pan.
Add carrots; cook until done.
Add frozen noodles; cook 5 minutes, then add soups and mushrooms.
Stir gently and cook 5 minutes.
Add chicken, and it's ready to eat!

title: delicious dessert
directions: *Drain fruit and save juice.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Simmer sauce mix, tomato sauce and water 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef in skillet; mix sauce with ground beef.
Place tortillas in baking dish; add 1/2 of meat mixture, then place more tortillas in baking dish and rest of meat mixture.
Cover with cheese and bake about 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix in order given and bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
When cool, dust top with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry jello fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water and stir until well blended. Add strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour half of mixture into 8 x 8-inch dish and freeze until set.
Spread sour cream over top, then pour remaining mixture and refrigerate until set.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In small bowl, beat eggs gently with fork.
In medium bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs from small bowl, carrots and pecans.
Stir together by hand.
Combine medium bowl with ingredients in large bowl.
Stir all ingredients well; do not use mixer.
Pour into 3 round pans.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done. Frost.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fattoush(the peasant salad)
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Add oil, lemon juice (preferably fresh), salt and sumac.
Mix.
Chill at least an hour. Just before serving, add croutons.
Toss lightly and serve.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine butter and peanut butter in a 2 quart glass bowl. Cover with a paper towel and microwave on high 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Press into an 11x7x1 1/2 baking dish.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 8 x 8 x 2 baking pan. Arrange apples in pan. Mix remaining ingredients with fork. Sprinkle over apples. Bake until apples are tender and topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes. Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla, blending well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt and blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: spinach egg drop soup
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain well.
Melt butter in a large saucepan. Add spinach and garlic; saute 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often. Beat together eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir egg mixture into spinach.
Immediately add broth and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.

title: cinnamon glazed almonds
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Place butter in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan. Place pan in oven to melt butter. Beat egg whites with salt until frothy; gradually add sugar. Beat until stiff peaks are formed. Fold in almonds and cinnamon. Pour almond mixture into pan and toss with butter. Bake approximately 40 minutes, tossing every 10 minutes, until almonds are crisp. Serve or store in airtight container.

title: appeloch kaffekaka(apple coffee cake)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir in wet ingredients and blend; then stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove, sprinkle with confections sugar.
Serve warm.

title: meal-in-one
directions: In a large casserole dish, place potatoes, a layer of onions and a layer of tomatoes.
Brown hamburger and spread on top of tomatoes.
Sprinkle rice over top and lay bacon on top of this. Add cold water to casserole until it reaches the top of the ingredients.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry dream dessert
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy sourdough flapjacks
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Beat egg; add milk.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Stir in yeast.
Allow batter to stand at room temperature for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not stir.
Bake on hot greased skillet or griddle.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add water and vanilla. Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts. Chill 4 hours. Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes (will not brown). Remove from pan; cool slightly. Roll in confectioners sugar. Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: garlic dip
directions: Blend artichoke hearts in a food processor.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with Fritos.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and toss with mayonnaise.
Delicious use for leftover ham.

title: hot or cold queso
directions: Boil green chiles, Ro-Tel, onion and garlic until onion is tender.
Add milk and stir continuously.
Add cheese and stir over medium heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 10 servings.

title: almond joy bars
directions: Line two large cookie sheets with waxed paper. Set large wire cooling rack on paper; set aside. Place coconut in large bowl; set aside. Place corn syrup in a 1 c. glass measure. Microwave on high (100%) 1 minute or until syrup boils; immediately pour over coconut. Work warm syrup into coconut using the back of a wooden spoon until coconut is thoroughly coated. This takes a little time, and, yes, there is enough syrup. Using 1 level measuring tablespoon of coconut, shape into a ball by squeezing coconut firmly in palm of one hand, then rolling in both palms. (Hint: measure out all the coconut, then roll into balls.) Place 2 inches apart on wire rack. Let dry 10 minutes. Reroll coconut balls so there are no loose ends of coconut sticking out. Place milk chocolate and shortening in a 4 cup measure or 1 1/2 qt. microwave safe bowl. Microwave on high 1 to 2 minutes or until mixture can be stirred smooth and is glossy; stirring once or twice. Working quickly, spoon 1 level measuring tablespoon of the chocolate over each coconut ball, making sure chocolate coats and letting excess chocolate drip onto waxed paper. While chocolate coating is still soft, lightly press whole almond on top of each. Let stand to set; place in refrigerator. Store in a single layer in an airtight container. Keeps best if refrigerated. Makes about 26.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, milk, egg, oil and vanilla together.
Set aside. Then mix dry ingredients together and then mix all ingredients. Pour in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 10 muffins.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, bouillon and margarine in large saucepan.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Add milk and reduce heat to low.
Cook until heated.
Add pepper. (Thicken with potato flakes if needed.)
Pour into serving bowls.
Top with bacon crumbs and cheese.
Serve with cornbread.
Yields 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch casserole or cake pan. Sprinkle bread cubes and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart glass casserole.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Cover with glass lid.
Microwave about 5 to 6 minutes on High or until meat is browned.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients; re-cover.
Microwave 14 to 18 minutes on Medium-high or until hot.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: *Omit salt and baking powder if using self-rising flour.

title: sun-drop cola pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add cola and beat well.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: In a skillet, brown chicken pieces in oil.
Place in baking dish large enough to hold all ingredients.
To skillet, add onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add catsup, water, lemon juice, brown sugar, Worcestershire, vinegar, prepared mustard, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes; skim off fat.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn chicken twice while cooking.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: crispy, crunchy cereal treats
directions: Set cereal aside in large bowl.
In saucepan, add sugar, margarine and syrup.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Boil 3 additional minutes.
Pour over cereal.
Mix well.
Spray Pam into mold (first time only); fill crispy mold with mixture.
Remove immediately from mold.
Place on wax paper.
Let set up 1 hour.
Seal finished product in plastic wrap.
Makes approximately 25 shapes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add vanilla and lemon extract or juice.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour a little at a time.
Spread out on greased jelly roll pan.
Mark with back of knife into squares.
Drop a tablespoon of pie filling into each section.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While warm, dust with powdered sugar (sift on in strainer).
Cool in pan.

title: "streusel pumpkin pie"
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
In large bowl, whisk together eggs, pumpkin, evaporated milk, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice.
Place one pie crust on preheated baking sheet.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake on preheated baking sheet 30 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Prepare lemonade as directed, add thawed strawberries and ice cubes. Add ginger ale just before serving. Makes 1 1/2 gallons of punch.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine and syrup.
Boil 5 minutes. Add salt, vanilla, soda and cream of tartar (it should foam up). Pour over popcorn and nuts.
Put in dish and bake at 250° to 275° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread out after removing from oven.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Add milk.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 9 or 10-inch pan.

title: stove top bread pudding
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Tear bread into pieces in bottom of skillet.
Beat eggs and stir in sugar, warm milk and vanilla.
Sprinkle raisins over the bread.
Pour egg mixture evenly over all.
Cover with heavy-duty aluminum foil tightly.
Cook over low heat about 20 minutes.
If custard is set, pudding is done. Cool in skillet and cut in wedges.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix together pumpkin, shortening and water. Add dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes. Add 2 beaten eggs and mix one more minute. Stir in chopped nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees. Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture.
Blend well.
Add oatmeal and raisins. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from baking sheets and cool on racks.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Combine together sugar, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric, vinegar and water.
Wash and chop or grind vegetables coarsely. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand all night.
Rinse and drain in morning.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions until golden.
Add meat and garlic; brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf and serve over spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole (1)
directions: Grease 9 X 13 cake pan.
Spread hash browns in pan, salt and pepper well.
Beat eggs, milk, red hot, salt and pepper.
Add green peppers, onion, mushrooms and green chilies to egg mixture. Pour over hash browns.
Spread cheese over top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamed crab and spinach soup
directions: Drain and separate canned crab, reserving liquid, or defrost, drain and slice frozen crab, also reserving liquid.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and chop coarsely.

title: veal goulash
directions: Brown meat.

Bring tomato sauce and Sloppy Joes mix to a boil; add meat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring often (prevent sticking). Just before serving, remove from heat and stir in sour cream. Garnish with parsley.
Serve on noodles.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and add water to make 1 1/2 cups. Heat and pour over Jell-O.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
In oven over medium-low heat, melt 1/4 cup butter, peanut butter and marshmallows.
Add cereal. Press into pan.
Drizzle with melted chocolate; chill.
Slice. Makes 36.

title: deviled pecans
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt oleo.
Combine remaining ingredients. Stir until pecans are coated with hot sauce.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Combine cake mix and oats.
Stir in margarine until mixture is crumbly (mix with hands towards end).
Put 3 cups of mixture in a 9 inch x 13 inch pan and press down firmly. Combine jam and water and spoon over crumb mixture.
Spread evenly to within 1/4 inch of edge.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.	Make top even by patting firmly.	Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.	Yield:	10-12 servings as a desert or 24-30 bars as cookies.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Add enough milk to make it spread easily.

title: blondies
directions: Beat eggs; add butter and sugar.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Mix flour and nuts.
Add to egg mixture along with vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fruit salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and chill.

title: grandma dew's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks with milk and pour into sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil and then cook for 15 minutes. Pour into a baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown in oven.
Makes 1 pie.
Serve warm or cold.

title: marie's white potato pie
directions: Combine
all
ingredients in order listed and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Mix all ingredients well; pour into baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Dot Ritz crackers with butter.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Coat shrimp with all seasoning.
Saute butter, onions, parsley, lemons, Worcestershire, liquid crab boil and all season.
Place in oven under broiler until pink, then pour sauce on them.
Turn down to 400°.
Add a can of beer.
Cook until broken away from shell, approximately 15 minutes.
Let soak until desired flavor.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels,
sugar and margarine, press into sheet pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Cream together sugar, cream cheese, Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzels and seal all edges.
Mix jello, water and strawberries, let stand until slightly set.
Pour over
cream
cheese mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour and soda.
Mix well.
Add chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: super punch
directions: Mix just before serving.
Add sherbet; stir gently.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Use large bowl, mix cake mix with yeast, then gradually add water and flour.
Beat with mixer, then scrape sides of bowl. Place in greased bowl and let raise until double in bulk.
Punch down and make into balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown on top.
By using RapidRise yeast, you can prepare rolls while cooking dinner.
Start rolls and turn on your oven first to preheat.
May be baked in muffin pans.

title: cornetti
directions: Mix water, yeast, oil and salt together and mix well.
Add flour; knead very well.
Put bowl over dough; let rest 15 minutes. Knead well again and let rise in a warm place (warm oven is fine), about 30 minutes.
Knead a little more and divide into 12 balls.
Roll 2 balls loosely, like sausage.
Put the 2 together and crimp tightly in the middle.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, sprinkled with cornmeal on bottom.
Let rise in warm place, 25 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or a little more if you want them crispy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and margarine. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well again.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix pickles, water and lime.
Stir a couple of times and soak 24 hours.
After soaking, rinse pickles 3 times.
Add to pickles the vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and pickling spice.
Let set overnight.
Then cook 35 minutes and jar, open kettle method. Makes about 6 quarts.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and mix well.
Spread 1/2 the batter in a greased 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Peel, core and cut apples into 1/8.
Arrange apples over the batter in a neat circle.
Pour rest of the batter over the apples.
Spread evenly.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Let cool. Remove ring of pan.
Enjoy.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a large heated, oiled skillet at 350° for 30 minutes, or until firm and lightly browned. This is very moist.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water; drain and dice.
Cook bacon; drain and chop.
Using 2 tablespoons of bacon fat, cook onion until brown.
Blend the flour, dry mustard, salt and sugar with onion; stir in water.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons of hot mixture to beaten egg.
Stir into rest of mixture; add vinegar and reheat.
Pour hot dressing over hot potatoes; mix in bacon.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Prepare the day before.
Cook sausage until done; drain and set aside.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix altogether; pour into greased baking dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs and season with garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fruit squares
directions: Put all fruits through food chopper.

Add peanut butter and condensed milk. Mix well and press into bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan that has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Smooth surface of candy and sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter in 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until a wooden toothpick comes out clean.
For a square pan, bake 45 minutes.
Cool pan 10 minutes; remove and cool.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting on top, sides and between layers and sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
"One of my favorite recipes."

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 1/4-1/2 inch strips.
Sprinkle with paprika and set aside.
Heat oil in skillet and saute meat for about 5 minutes.
Add bell pepper, celery, onion, garlic, beef bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15-20 minutes. Combine soy sauce, water and cornstarch.
Stir well.
Add to skillet and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Turn off heat.
Place tomato pieces on top (do not stir them in).
Cover and let steam for 5-10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add crumbled bacon and remaining ingredients.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: copper dollars
directions: Slice carrots 1/4 inch thick.
Slice onion and pepper.
Layer carrots, onion and pepper.
Heat sugar, tomato soup, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Let stand overnight.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks refrigerated.
Serves 16.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine baking soda, cut up dates and hot water and let cool. Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, salt, flour and chopped nuts.
Add to date mixture and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours. Makes 1 loaf.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cups blueberries into pastry shell; spread evenly and set aside.
Combine 1 cup blueberries, sugar, cornstarch and water in a medium saucepan; cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and vanilla and cool.
Pour over blueberries in pastry shell.
Chill.
Spoon whipped topping around edge; garnish with 1/4 cup blueberries. Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: apricot dessert(can use any flavor you like)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
While water is hot, dissolve cream cheese.
When melted, add 2 cups cold water and chill until firm.
Take out and add medium size Cool Whip and crushed pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Keep in refrigerator.
(Can use any flavor of choice and fruit of your choice.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in shortening; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Uncover; cook until desired consistency.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Blend in flavorings.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with white icing and pineapple filling.
Top with grated coconut.

title: harvest hamburger casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, combine beef, onion, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole dish. Layer the potatoes, flour, veggies and green pepper on top. Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: fay's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water and set aside.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Add remaining flour.
Put in greased bowl, turning to cover dough.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or up to 5 days.

title: wild onions and eggs
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain, then crumble.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in a skillet and stir in flour.
Slowly stir in milk. Pour half of the sauce into a greased casserole.
Add half of the onions, half of the bacon and half of the eggs.
Repeat the layers, ending with the white sauce.
Sprinkle with crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Fry onions and celery in butter.
Cook limas until tender and drain.
Put all other ingredients with limas.
Put mixture in buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake until crumbs are brown.
Use the butter in which the onions and celery were cooked to butter the bread crumbs.
Use liquid from cooked beans to thin the soup a little.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add 1/2 cup milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Remove from heat; stir in chicken.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine cookie mix, add egg whites and stir until well blended.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Cool totally and combine confectioners sugar, water and vanilla.
Then blend and drizzle over top.
Cut into squares.

title: arroz con chili verde(rice with green chili)
directions: Add rice to boiling water. Stir. Cover and let stand 3 minutes. Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Put rice in dish. Add rest of the ingredients. Bake until cheese melts and mixture is heated thoroughly. You can do this in crock-pot. Just mix in crock-pot and heat for 1 hour on high, then on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash, trim and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems and chop fine. Melt butter and oil; add onion, garlic, basil, salt, pepper and mushroom stems.
Saute until tender.
Remove from heat; add bread crumbs, crab meat and mustard.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Mix soup and milk.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, add potatoes and cover with soup mixture.
Put oleo over this and add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until Bisquick looks golden.

title: yogurt (laban)
directions: Heat milk on low fire until it comes to a scald (froth to top of pot).
Remove from fire and cool enough so that you could immerse a finger and count to 10.
Add 1/2 cup warm milk to starter and stir about 10 minutes.
Pour into container (plastic preferred).
Cover, then cover with warm towel or cloth.
Let set in warm place about 6 hours without disturbing.
Refrigerate. Reserve starter for next batch.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Split English muffins and spread Cheez Whiz.
Add small amount of crabmeat to English muffin.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Let sit 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Bring brown sugar, cooking sherry and oleo to a boil to melt. Mix all ingredients together and heat in a casserole dish until bubbly. Delicious with pork or chicken.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes (lightly salted).
Cut the bacon in 1/4 to 1/2 inch pieces and cook over low heat.
Drain over paper towel (save fat from bacon).
(Do not let potatoes get too done, they slice easier when firm.)
Add sliced onion to sliced potatoes.
Combine vinegar, hot water, snipped parsley and celery seed, plus put in bacon fat.
Add as needed.
Should be sort of juicy.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook and drain off 2/3 grease from onions and bacon; crumble bacon.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix meal, onion, salt and pepper.
Dissolve soda in milk and add to meal mixture.
Beat well and drop from spoon into hot fat and brown on both sides.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Pour over green beans in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cover with onion rings and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chill 1 to 2 hours and serve.

title: micro green beans(diet)
directions: Cook beans 10 to 12 minutes in package.
Mix remaining ingredients in 2-cup glass cup.
Stir and cook 1 to 3 minutes until glassy on Full power.
Pour over beans.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill all ingredients.
Seve with bite size pieces of raw celery, raw carrots, raw green peppers, raw cucumbers, raw cauliflower, raw radishes, raw zucchini, raw squash and raw broccoli.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread	crushed
pineapple
with juice in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over cake mix.
Cut butter in small squares and layer over	cake. Press in pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until browned.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: sam's chili(a vegetarian weight watchers recipe)
directions: I always double this recipe.
Simmer easy and very satisfying.

title: potato salad casserole
directions: Slice potatoes.
Add cheese, onion, parsley, eggs and salt. Mix well.
Now add soup and sour cream that have been mixed together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat soup and sour cream together.
In 9 x 12-inch glass dish, combine potatoes, cheese and margarine.
Add soup and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs or etc.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: goat bake
directions: Heat oven to 375`.
Grease well a 10-inch cast-iron skillet. Have ingredients at room temperature.
Crumble goat cheese with Ricotta.
Beat well the eggs and mix with cheeses.
Add seasonings.
Pour mixture into skillet and put in oven.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and French bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: julienne carrots with walnuts
directions: Scrape carrots; remove ends.
Cut into julienne strips.
Add carrots and onions to 1 inch of salted boiling water.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 25 minutes.
Drain; toss with butter and walnuts.
Season to taste.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand 30 minutes at room temperature.

title: golden chicken bake
directions: Mix cornflake crumbs and margarine; set aside.	Combine all other ingredients.	You
may
also add mushrooms and green or red peppers to taste.
Spread
into
a 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish (or larger if
more
ingredients
are
used).
Add
cornflake mixture to top.
Bake at
for 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: easy chili
directions: In large pot, brown meat and cut up onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: potato chowder
directions: In a large Dutch oven or kettle, combine potatoes, onion, carrot, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and bouillon cubes.
Add enough water to just cover vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not drain.
Scald milk. Remove 1 1/2 cups milk and add butter and flour to the milk, stirring with a wire whisk.
Add remaining hot milk to undrained vegetables, then stir in thickened milk mixture.
Stir until blended.
Simmer for 15 minutes on low heat.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onions.
Add beans and barbecue sauce.
Cook on low heat until done.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green peppers in skillet. Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, ketchup, and pepper and heat. Alternate meat mixture and cheese slices in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange biscuits around edge of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: post toastie cookies
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: bacon casserole
directions: Put bread into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss and cover in cheese.
Mix milk, eggs, mustard and salt, then pour over cheese.
Top with bacon and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serves 8.

title: sugar plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Beat until mixed well.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: *Applesauce may be substituted for part or all of oil to reduce fat content.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Melt butter; add milk and brown sugar.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add 1/2 of powdered sugar.
Cool slightly. Add vanilla and rest of sugar.
Beat well.
If too thick, add more milk.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute livers and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until liver is just cooked.
Put mixture through food grinder.
Heat cognac until reduced to 1/4 cup.
Blend with
liver mixture.
Beat in salt, thyme, anchovy paste, cream cheese and butter using electric mixer.
Chill until firm.
Can be rolled in chopped parsley after refrigeration.
Unmolds easily if you line mold with damp cheesecloth.

title: chicken drumettes
directions: Cut wings in pieces.
Set aside bony tips for soup or other use.
In a shallow pan, mix soy sauce, brown sugar, mustard and garlic powder until well blended.
Put in the wings and turn to coat.
Marinate 2 hours in refrigerator.
Bake in same pan 1 hour at 375°.
Baste frequently with pan juices.
Serve hot. Yields 36 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick of melted butter. Press in bottom of 9 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and butter (melted).
Add eggs and nuts.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber chips
directions: Wash and slice cukes.
Add sliced onion and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Mix sugar and vinegar; add spices.
Pour over cucumbers. Put into freezer containers.
Place in freezer; use when desired.

title: speedy potato chowder
directions: In 3-quart pan over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towels.
Save 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings.

title: two-way casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: fresh cherry pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine cherries, sugar, tapioca, lemon peel and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Fill a pastry lined 9-inch pie plate with cherry mixture; dot with butter or margarine.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge high.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; bake for 25 to 30 minutes more or until golden.
Cool on a wire rack before serving.
Serves 8.

title: tomato and basil penne
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer a few minutes.
Add seasonings and cream and simmer a few minutes more.
Stir in cooked pasta.

title: coconut toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Blend in flour, press evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Spread with topping.
Bake 25 minutes longer or until topping is golden brown.
Cool slightly, cut into bars.
Makes 32 cookies.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Cut off root ends of onions.
Peel and slice crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate slices into rings.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine ingredients into large mixing bowl, stirring occasionally.
Chill for a couple of hours.
Serve as a side dish.

title: smoked pork chops on a potato apple bed
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender, about 10 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine the potatoes, apples and onions; put in dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Sear pork chops by rubbing fatty ends around hot frypan and brown quickly on both sides. Place chops on potatoes.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Pour horseradish sauce over all and bake another 30 minutes.

title: sausage skillet supper
directions: Cut sausage into chunks.
Combine with rice, cream of celery soup, water and butter in large skillet on medium heat.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in peas and mushrooms, drained.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: becky scott's fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Set aside to cool.
Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add 1 cup hot water.
Boil until thick and clear.
Take off to cool.
Add jello and boil a few minutes until completely dissolved.
Line cooled pie shell with strawberries (whole).
Pour syrup over strawberries.
Chill one hour before serving.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Line muffin tin with paper cups, fill and freeze.
To serve, remove carefully to preserve the crinkled edges.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon and set aside to cool.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender.
Let set for several hours to combine flavors.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Shape dough in 1 1/2-inch balls, flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Start peeling and cleaning shrimp; about halfway through cleaning, put 2 sticks butter in wok and melt.
Put in lemon juice to taste (about 1/3 cup), 10 cloves garlic or garlic powder (about 1 1/2 teaspoons), 1/8 teaspoon of white pepper and 1/8 teaspoon dill seed.
Boil water for linguini
noodles.
Finish peeling shrimp.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat onto a jellyroll pan, seam together, and bake according to package directions.
After it is cool, mix mayonnaise and cream cheese together and spread on top of baked crescent rolls.
Chop up broccoli, cauliflower and green onions. Place on top.
Last, add Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses.
Serve chilled.

title: marinated mackerel
directions: Thoroughly
clean
fish.
Remove
heads and tails.
Cut the fish into slices about 3/4 to 1-inch thick.
Cook the fish in the salted water for about 7 to 8 minutes.
Don't overcook. Pour into bowl.
Cover
the
fish with the water the fish was cooked
in. Add
onions, peppercorns and bay leaves.
Let sit for a
couple of
hours.
Serve.
Can be used as appetizer or main dish. Oh, so good!

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Place in large saucepan, margarine, oil, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil.
Add flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
This batter is very thin. Pour into large cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix water and fat; heat to a boil.
Add flour and salt and mix thoroughly; stir.
Cook until ingredients are well blended and dough does not stick to sides (do not cook too long) and mixture is hot.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time.
Beat until well mixed. Drop by tablespoons onto oiled pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package, drain.
In large casserole dish combine all ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle a little extra cheese on top, approximately 5 minutes before done.

title: green rice bake(microwave)
directions: In a 1-quart micro-proof casserole place 2 tablespoons water, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and broccoli.
Cover and cook on High (maximum power) for 5 minutes.
Stir once during cooking time to break up pieces.
Cook onions in butter in a 1 1/2-quart micro-proof casserole on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in soup, rice and broccoli. Top with cheese.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes on High.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn after 5 minutes of cooking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry treat
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, nuts and butter. Spread in a flat pan, bake in a 320° oven for 20 minutes, stirring several times. Cool. Sprinkle 2/3 of crumb mixture in 9 x 12 pan.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket on double sheet of heavy duty foil.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over brisket-wrap tightly in foil.
Bake 300 degrees for one hour per pound.
Do not cook over 4 hours.
Chill in refrigerator overnight, must be cold to slice properly.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line jelly roll pan with graham crackers. Boil the sugar, butter, milk, egg and crushed graham crackers. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add the coconut.
Spread thinly over crackers. Top with whole graham crackers.
Frost with Chocolate Chip Frosting. Cover and cut next morning when soft.

title: lemon orange cake
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 375°.
Bake cake as directed on box in round pans.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: peach bread
directions: To make peach puree, use 6 to 8 medium peaches with skins on, put through blender, or 3 (15 ounce) cans of peaches, drained. Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add peach puree, dry ingredients and almond flavoring. Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: wacky cake (cocoa)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together in an 8 x 8-inch pan the following:
flour, salt, cocoa, soda and granulated sugar.
Make 3 holes in the ingredients.
In one put the vanilla, the second, the vinegar, and the third, the salad oil.
Pour 1 cup water over the whole thing.
Mix well and bake for 30 minutes.
The cake does not stick, even though the pan is ungreased.

title: pasta vegetable soup
directions: Heat all but macaroni to boil.
Stir in macaroni and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until macaroni is done.

title: low-fat fruit trifle
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Mix pineapple and oranges.
Mix pudding as directed on package using skim milk.
Layer half each of cake pieces, fruit mixture and pudding.
Repeat.
Spread on whipped topping.
Garnish with chopped pecans and cherries.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: cherry cheese brownie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Spread lightly into 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned corn relish(microwave recipe)
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine corn and 2 tablespoons of water; cook, covered, at High for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring once.
Drain in colander.
In same casserole, mix sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vinegar and 1/3 cup water.
Add corn, celery, green pepper, pimento, onion and seasonings.
Cook, uncovered, at High for 5 minutes until mixture is thickened and bubbly, stirring after each minute.
Cook, covered, at High for 3 minutes more.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Stir before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: ham and dried limas
directions: Rinse dried lima beans in a colander and remove any stones or other fishy looking, non-bean type matter.

In a Dutch oven, bring beans, ham and enough water to fill the pan 3/4 full to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and add the chopped onion, salt, pepper and a generous sprinkle of dried red pepper (like you put on pizza) to taste.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until beans are tender (may take from 1 to 3 hours, depending on personal taste).
Add additional water as needed to prevent mixture from sticking to pan.

title: curried rabbit with vegetables
directions: Cut up rabbit into serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt, curry powder and paprika in a paper or plastic bag.
Add the rabbit pieces and shake until each piece is thoroughly covered. Brown the meat in oil in a large skillet.
Add 1 cup water, cover and simmer for about 1 hour.
Add the vegetables and the bay leaves; cook an additional 30 minutes or until carrots are tender. Remove rabbit and vegetables.
Add sour cream and garlic powder to the skillet.
Heat until thickened for gravy.

title: sweet potato souffle with crunchy topping
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: lumberjack soup
directions: Heat all the ingredients in a 3 to 4-quart saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Pour into an ovenproof dish. Cover with toasted Italian bread.
Cover with grated Mozzarella or Swiss cheese.
Bake in oven until bubbly and cheese melts.
Serves 4 people.

title: banana blueberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom of 2 loaf pans. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in oats. Add oil, eggs, bananas and blueberries, stirring just until mixed. Pour batter into greased pans. Bake for 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans. Cool completely on wire racks. Makes 2 loaves.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Remove the dark leaves and put aside from the cabbage.
Also, cut the core slightly before simmering the cabbage in a pot of water.
It makes it easier to remove the leaves.
Set them aside to cool.
Put a few strips of bacon on bottom of roaster or pan. Lay the stuffed cabbage leaves on top.
Then pour in the cabbage rolls, the soup mixture and 1 teaspoon vinegar.
After they are all in, add the sauerkraut and a few more bacon strips and broth.

title: pecan bars
directions: Using pastry blender, blend together flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle evenly with pecans; set aside.
In a small saucepan, cook remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2/3 cup butter over medium heat until surface is bubbly.
Pour over pecan and flour layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawbananut cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs and mix well.
Add milk, strawberries
and bananas.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together; add to milk mixture, mix well; add flavoring and dry jello and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven.
Make as layers or in
a
tube pan.
To frost, use strawberry juice thickened with powdered sugar.

title: oven-buttered cornsticks
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
In mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix and corn; stir until soft dough forms.
Knead about 15 strokes on lightly floured surface.
Roll to 6 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Roll in melted butter in pan and arrange in single layer. Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 20.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Combine the flour, salt, white sugar, baking powder and brown sugar together.
Blend in Crisco and butter.
Reserve 3 to 4 handfuls of this mixture.
To the remainder, add egg, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Pour into pan and reserved mixture on top.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon-sugar mixture and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken almond
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and pour off excess grease.
Cut up bell pepper.
Put onions and pepper in skillet.
Cook about 12 minutes until tender.
Pour onions, sausage and bell pepper in large pan.
Add salt, Lipton soup, slivered almonds, water and rice (steamed until done).
Cover with foil.
Put cube of butter in pan and pour in Wheaties.
Stir until well coated with butter.
Add grated cheese.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco, sugar and egg.
In separate bowl, mix together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to the first mixture with a wooden spoon.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in colored sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
It's great for dipping strawberries, grapes, apples and bananas.

title: chicken and vegetables
directions: With about 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a Dutch oven, saute chicken lightly (I remove the skins) and remove from pan.

title: chicken in oven
directions: Pan-fry chicken real fast. Remove. Add soup and water. Bake in oven 2 hours, covered, at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, egg, milk and chopped nuts together.
Slowly mix in Bisquick and beat hard for 30 seconds.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and baking powder.
Pour over melted butter.
Add fruit.
Don't stir! Sprinkle extra cup of sugar on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl stir together flour, baking powder, salt ginger, soda and cloves.
Set aside.
In large bowl beat together brown sugar and shortening until well blended.
Beat in eggs. Add pumpkin and milk; mix well.

title: oreo pizza
directions: Stir cookie pieces into prepared brownie batter.
Spread in greased 4 inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350 for 18-20 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle marshmallows over hot brownies and bake 2-3 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed.
Sprinkle with nuts and candies pressing lightly into softened marshmallows.
Cool.

title: different banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas and vanilla wafers.
Mix until thickened.
(Use only 1/2 of the small 6 ounce Cool Whip.) Layer wafers (may be crumbled), sliced bananas and filling.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and whole vanilla wafers.

title: baked tuna chow mein casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in butter.
Mix in rest of ingredients; pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup chow mein noodles. Bake 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: *Or 2 tablespoons of pumpkin pie spices.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs with milk and flour.
Add salt, pepper, sausage and cheese.
Pour into pie crusts.
Sprinkle some cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or stick to see when done.

title: biscuits for 150
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together until well blended.
Cut shortening with with pastry.
Add milk and stir together.
Roll out small batches.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: best ever and easy salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream; add to vegetables. Mix all together and let stand a few hours.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Separate crescent rolls and press over bottom and sides of pizza pan.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach, drain well.
Mix all ingredients together. Taste just like Anderson's famous dip.
Best with pumpernickel bread.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, peanut butter, shortening, margarine and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours. Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar in crisscross pattern.
Bake until light brown, 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes, remove from cookie sheet.

title: florentine party appetizers
directions: In large bowl combine eggs, soup and cheese spread.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and green onions; mix well.
Unroll crescent rolls, but do not separate.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased baking pan.
Gently press seams together.
Spread spinach mixture over dough.
Top with pimento.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Serve hot.
Makes 40 appetizers.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast and soda to buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until crumbly.
Pour in buttermilk mixture and work together with fork. Store in a tightly covered container and use as needed.
Roll to 1/2-inch on pastry cloth and cut with biscuit cutter.
Do not let rise. Dough will keep at least 10 days in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces.
Add cheese, onions and sweet peas. Add enough Miracle Whip to mix up well.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: sweet bread
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Mix in sugar.
Let set until dissolved. Blend dry ingredients.
Mix in yeast mixture.
Knead for 5 minutes. Cover and let rise.
Knead again. Roll out and add anything you want, such as raisins, nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Let your imagination go!
Fold into loaves. Place in greased pans and let rise. Bake at 350° for 35 to 60 minutes, depending on size of loaf.

title: glamorous green beans
directions: Take drained beans and bunch together in small bundles.
(Two cans should make ten bundles.)
Wrap one slice of bacon around each bundle and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt & pepper.
Mix enough brown sugar with water to make a thick syrup.
Poor over beans.

title: fresh fried okra
directions: Wash and slice okra.
Leave damp.
Salt to taste.
Sprinkle with flour, shaking all loose flour off.
Put in heated skillet with 1/4 cup oil.
Cook on low.
Turn often to keep from burning. Done when golden brown.
Add more oil to skillet if needed.

title: chili chicken salad
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add first 7 ingredients; process until a paste forms, scraping sides of processor bowl occasionally.
Place chicken breast halves in a shallow dish; spread onion mixture evenly over both sides of each piece.
Cover; let marinate in refrigerator 20 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and and vanilla and lemon extract. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs (1 at a time), beating well after each addition.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out on floured counter.
Cut into doughnut shapes.
Drop into hot grease until golden brown, then flip over and do other side.
Roll in powdered sugar or regular sugar.
Keep in airtight container with a piece of bread to keep fresh.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan on medium heat. Bring to boil. Take off heat. Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter; beat until smooth. Put into a greased cake pan. Put into refrigerator to chill.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, flour, water, syrup and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil over low heat.
Let boil hard 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until firm. Pour into buttered pan.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and shell.
Pack in a 1/2-gallon jar.
In large saucepan, heat vinegar, sugar and pickling spice.
Pour hot vinegar over eggs.
Cover.
Put in fridge overnight.
Use as needed.
You can also add
a sliced
onion and a 28 ounce can of whole beets to eggs to use as Easter relish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup and sugar.
Add melted butter, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake about 50 minutes in 325° oven.

title: meatball minestrone soup
directions: In mixing bowl, combine meat, egg, onions, crumbs, salt and pepper.
Shape into 30 one-inch balls.
In a large saucepan, brown meatballs on all sides.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni and parsley.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add macaroni; simmer for 10 minutes or until tender. Stir in parsley.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Layer green pepper, onion, broccoli and shredded cheese. Place in a glass deep dish pie plate.
Mix eggs, Bisquick, milk and salt.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice skillet
directions: In a large skillet, cook the bacon until crisp; drain.
Leave 1 tablespoon of drippings in pan.
Cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 35 minutes. Crumble bacon on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry-almond cream pie
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with 1/2 cup cranberry sauce; spread evenly over bottom of pastry shell.
Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar, cornstarch and remaining cranberry sauce; blend well and spread carefully over cream cheese layer.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Combine flour and remaining 1/3 cup brown sugar; blend in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in almonds.
Sprinkle over pie.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more, or until center of pie is firm.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute mushrooms and pepper in oleo.
Make white sauce.
Add chicken to mushroom mixture.
Blend in white sauce and simmer for a few minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together the Rice Krispies, brown sugar, melted butter, coconut and chopped nut meats.
Press half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften the ice cream and spread it over the layer of the Rice Krispie mixture.
Cover with the rest of the Rice Krispie mixture and press evenly over the top.
Put in freezer until firm. For serving, cut in pieces and top with a tablespoon of cherry pie filling.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add strawberry Jell-O. Stir well and cool 2 to 3 hours.
Clean and drain berries.
Leave whole or slice.
Add to syrup.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipping cream.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Melt butter in a shallow baking dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll the chicken in butter mixture, coating both sides.
Arrange skin side down in a single layer in same dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.
Good served with Curried Rice.

title: apple pineapple crisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and spread the bottom with undrained pineapple.
Place apples on top of pineapple and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with dry cake mix and top with pecans.
Pour melted margarine over entire crisp.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Top with 1/3 cup Catalina dressing.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken with feta sauce
directions: On a sheet of waxed paper, sprinkle the chicken with the vinegar and thyme.	In a large, nonstick skillet, heat the oil. Cook the chicken until brown and cooked thoroughly, 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Transfer to a plate.
Sprinkle the flour and oregano over the pan juices.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Gradually whisk in the milk.
Cook until thick and bubbling, whisking constantly, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in the vegetables, cheese, and lemon juice.
Reduce heat and simmer until the cheese melts, about 2 minutes.
Place the rice on a large platter.
Top with
chicken.
Spoon the sauce over the chicken.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: fast pineapple pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk according to package directions.
In glass bowl, layer wafers, pineapple and pudding.
Chill.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Pour tomatoes into a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Cut bread into pieces and sprinkle on top of tomatoes.
Pour butter over bread pieces. Sprinkle brown sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less until crisp on top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat until soft the butter.
Add sugar and brown sugar gradually and blend until creamy.
Beat in egg, peanut butter, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Sift, measure and add flour.
Blend in.
Roll into small balls.
Place on greased pan.
Press flat with fork.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 minutes.

title: jumbo shrimp(with prosciutto and basil)
directions: Combine wine, oil, lemon juice, mustard, chopped basil and peppercorns.
Pour over shrimp in a shallow bowl.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 3 hours, turning shrimp occasionally. Prepare hot coals with generous amount of mesquite for grilling the shrimp.
Reserve marinade.
Wrap the middle of each shrimp with a basil leaf and then with a slice of Prosciutto.
Thread 4 shrimp lengthwise, starting at the head on each of 6 metal skewers. Grill, basting with reserved marinade for several minutes on each side.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 main course servings or 24 appetizers.

title: cranberry crunch - a la mode
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Combine rolled oats, flour and brown sugar in a mixing bowl.
Using two knives, cut in butter until crumbly.
Place half of this mixture in prepared pan.
Cover with cranberry sauce (if jellied sauce is used, crush with a fork).
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm; cut into squares and top with vanilla ice cream.

title: venison stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in crock-pot on low setting overnight or 8 to 10 hours.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, milk and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently mix in whipped topping.
Spread in bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Mixture will be thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk until well blended.
Spread over the cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: depression cocktail
directions: Shake all ingredients together with cracked ice.
Serves 8.

title: mexican garbage
directions: Place tortillas on bottom of pan, add browned hamburger meat, onion, green chilies and taco sauce mixture.
Then add can of soup.
Add more tortillas then top with grated cheese.
Put in oven at 350° to melt, about 30 minutes.

title: harvest apple pie
directions: Mix together sugars, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a small bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice in large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar mixture.
Toss gently to coat apples evenly. Arrange apples in pastry shell. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup sugar mixture. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 25 minutes or until apples are tender. Carefully pour warm cream over apples and bake 10 minutes longer.
Grated cheese may be added to top of pie about 5 minutes before removing from oven.

title: chile quesadillas
directions: Prepare guacamole and slice ripe olives for garnish.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup of cheese onto 3 tortillas.
Top each with 1/3 of chiles and 2 teaspoons salsa.
Cover with remaining tortillas, pressing gently in heated skillet over medium heat.
Heat, one at a time, for 2 minutes on each side or until cheese melts.

title: baked ham
directions: Wrap ham in aluminum foil.
Prick ham with fork.
Use half of 7-Up over ham first, then all of sweet potato juice and all of pineapple juice.
Cook for 1 hour in 400° oven.
After 1 hour, open foil, use the rest of 7-Up, then
use honey on top of ham. Sprinkle with lemon pepper and cook for 2 hours or until done. Cool and slice.

title: rice casserole
directions: Butter dish well. Mix ingredients well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a covered dish.

title: fudge candy
directions: It will be runny.
Put in refrigerator.
Double for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: *sparkling fruit mold
directions: Drain fruit; save juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add ginger ale.
Add cold water to fruit juice to make 1 3/4 cups; stir in jello.
Chill until partially set, then add fruit.
Pour into 2-quart container or mold.
Chill until firm.
Fold marshmallows into Cool Whip and then add Miracle Whip.
Spoon over jello mix and chill.
Garnish with toasted, shredded coconut, if desired.

title: pork sausage louisiana style
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix very well.
Keep cool.
May be stuffed in casings or made into patties.

title: berry cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over this, sprinkle the blueberries, sugar and boiling
water.
Bake
in
a
350°	oven
for 30 minutes.
The bottom will be like pudding when finished.	Can be served with milk, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Spread broccoli in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine chicken, mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup and lemon juice.
Spread on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese. Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter.
Spread on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dad's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and spinach; drain and place in large mixing bowl.
Add onion, rice and olives; mix thoroughly.
Mix soup and sour cream; add to vegetables.
Pour into large greased casserole and top with shredded cheese.
Cover with crushed whole wheat crackers and bake in a 325° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Tear up the slices of bread and place in baking dish. Fry bacon until crisp, drain, crumble and sprinkle over the bread. Sprinkle with the cheese.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
