Pour egg mixture over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Excellent served with fried potatoes and English muffins for brunch, lunch or dinner!

title: layered pear cream cheese mold
directions: Drain pears, reserving liquid.
Dice pears; set aside.
Add water to liquid to make 1 1/2 cups; bring to boil in small saucepan.
Stir boiling liquid into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold ginger ale and lemon juice.
Reserve 2 1/2 cups gelatin at room temperature.
Pour remaining gelatin into 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until thickened.
Arrange about 1/2 cup of the diced pears in thickened gelatin in mold.
Stir reserved 2 1/2 cups gelatin gradually into cream cheese in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until slightly thickened. Stir in remaining diced pears and pecans.
Spoon over gelatin layer in mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish as desired.

title: sausage-mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Combine eggs, milk, soup, mushrooms and mustard; mix well.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator, let stand 30 minutes. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Garnish with tomatoes and parsley.
(Tomato seed side up and 1 piece parsley on each side of a tomato.)
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked beans
directions: Arrange into baking dish and bake top with bacon strips on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna patties
directions: Crush crackers and mix all ingredients together and shape into patties.
Fry in light corn oil until golden brown.

title: mini-ham puffs(appetizers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop ham and onion finely.
Add cheese, egg, pepper and mustard.
Mix well.
Unroll entire package of crescent rolls into one large rectangle.
Cut into 24 small squares.
Place each square in a mini-tart pan.
Shape to fit pan. Place filling in tarts and bake for 15 minutes.
Yields 24 appetizers.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Cut like for pie crust until fine crumbs. Press into Pam sprayed jelly roll pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Add meat.
Cover and refrigerate.
Allow mixture to marinate for 24 hours.
Preheat oven to 100°.
Place jerky on oven racks.
Bake 2 hours and turn. For softer jerky, cook between 6 to 7 hours.
For harder jerky, cook longer.

title: golden crumb broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 10 minutes.
Drain and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over broccoli. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge
directions: Grease a jelly roll pan or a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Combine the chocolate and marshmallows and set aside.
Mix the sugar, butter and milk in a heavy pot, stirring to combine well. Gradually bring to a boil over low heat, stirring until the sugar dissolves.
Wash down the sides of the pan with a pastry brush dipped in cold water.
Boil, stirring constantly, without touching the sides of pan for 5 minutes.
Add the chocolate mixture, the salt and vanilla.
Stir until the chocolate melts; add the nuts. Spread in pan.
Let stand until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Pour warm water into a large warm mixing bowl.
Put in dry yeast; let set until yeast is dissolved (5 to 10 minutes).
Add salt, sugar and oil; stir.
Add 4 cups flour; stir well.
Add 4 more cups flour; stir again.
Add 1 cup flour at a time; knead well until dough can be held on hand extended.
Knead on board or in bowl.
Put in a bowl to rise; cover top to prevent drying.
Let rise 2 times original size.
Work down to original size.
Make into 4 to 6 loaves.

title: chicken baskets
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese, parsley flakes, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add chopped chicken.
Stir. Put 1 tablespoon of mixture in center of crescent roll.
Fold into a triangle.
Pinch to seal edges.
Dip in butter, then bread crumbs.
Repeat.
Bake on a well-greased cookie sheet for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until golden.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, chicken soup and mushroom soup together.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Add salad dressing until smooth. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: citrus splash
directions: Pour juices into a large punch bowl.
Stir in water and crushed ice.
Top with lemon slices and raspberries.
Serves many.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Grease oblong baking dish. Layer chicken and broccoli in dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over broccoli.
Arrange cheese slices on soup mixture.
Mix Bisquick mix and butter until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with tomato slices if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture and mix until smooth. Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook stew meat until tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and onion. When veggies are tender, stir in stew mix, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened.

title: lemon orange rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake in pan 15 minutes, then prick with fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Meanwhile, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add orange juice. Pour carefully over warm cake.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Frost with 8 to 12 ounces Cool Whip.

title: chop suey
directions: Put celery and onion in pan, covered, with water and boil until tender.
In another pan, saute hamburger and mushrooms together in olive oil.
Add some Worcestershire sauce for color (2 tablespoons), then add in bean sprouts and vegetables.
Add the celery and onion when tender, along with its water (add more water if needed).
Add the molasses and simmer for about 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf(serving size: 6)
directions: Beat meat, eggs, crumbs, ketchup, Accent, water and soup mix thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with two strips of bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: celebration punch
directions: Mix strawberries, vodka, lemon juice, orange juice and water. Refrigerate until cold.
Pour cold mixture over ice cubes in punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale gently.
Garnish with mint sprigs. Makes 28 servings (1/2 cup each).

title: raspberry-topped lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thickened and clear.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into crust.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: fiesta pasta
directions: Prepare pasta according to package and set aside.
In 12 inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat and saute zucchini, onion, Trappey's peppers and garlic for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, oregano, olives and salt and heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently until mixture thickens.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender.
Cool and shred coarsely. Melt oleo and add cheese, milk, flour and seasoning.
Fold in sour cream and onion.
Combine and place in baking dish and bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.
Top with cornflakes. Place back in oven for approximately 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar. Refrigerate for at least 6 hours. Roll and slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm. Yields 4 dozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix citric acid, boiling water and sugar and let stand for 24 hours.
Add cold water, food coloring, pineapple juice and orange juice to the first mixture and freeze.
Set out of freezer 4 to 5 hours before serving, then add chilled ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil water, add 1 teaspoon salt.
Add elbows.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Drain water.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Stir in butter.
Cut cheese into small cubes and add to macaroni.
Add milk and stir.
Add sour cream, if desired. Place in oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Take out and stir. Sprinkle pepper on top and place back in oven for 15 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sante fe burrito bake
directions: Put bread dough out to thaw so it has time to thaw and rise before you roll it out.
Then it's easy to manage.
Brown meat until pink is gone.
Stir in water, chilies and seasonings.
Add cereal and stir well.
Turn off heat and let cool somewhat.
Roll dough into a 10 x 15-inch oblong.
Place on baking sheet and spread out with hands if it draws up.

Do not grease baking sheet. Spread half the meat mixture down the center about 4-inches wide. Sprinkle cheese on top and then other half of meat mixture. Bring sides of dough up over filling and seal.
Roll over so seam side is down.
Brush with margarine and sprinkle lightly with chili powder or paprika.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Keeps well.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until hot.
Makes 8 cups.

title: pralines
directions: Have ready baking sheet covered with waxed paper. Bring 2 cups sugar and the milk to a boil.
Add pecans.
Let boil while you melt the remaining 1/2 cup sugar in a large skillet over low heat. Add melted sugar to other mixture and cook to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Remove from heat. Beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: oatmeal raisin drop cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and shortening or margarine. Beat in eggs, vanilla and 7 tablespoons raisin liquid.
Mix flour, soda, oatmeal and salt and add to mixture.
Add boiled raisins last.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage, cheese and egg casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with Crisco.
Mix eggs and milk.
Add dry mustard, salt, pepper, cheese, shredded bread and sausage. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together. Chill 2 to 3 hours. Shape into 2 balls. Roll in 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: potato cheddar casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Top with crushed cornflakes or Ritz crackers. Bake 20-30 minutes at 350° till brown and bubbly.

title: fruit roll
directions: *Use 2 or more kinds of candied fruit.

title: deep chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
(Will be runny.)
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: banana royale pie
directions: In
a
large bowl, combine yogurt, milk, rum and pudding mix. With
wire
whisk,
beat
until
thickened.
Fold whipped topping into
pudding
mixture until no streaks remain.
Spoon half of pudding mixture into crust.
Peel and slice the banana; arrange in
single
layer
on pie.
Spoon remaining mixture on top. Sprinkle
toasted coconut around the edge; refrigerate 30 minutes or
until
dessert
time.
Garnish top with additional banana slices, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: harry's humorers
directions: Cream
the softened butter and sugar.
Add eggs, molasses and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon and soda.
Gradually add	to creamed
mixture.
Stir
in
oats,	raisins, nuts and chocolate. Drop
by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake
in
350° oven
for
to
14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool
on wire racks and store in airtight container. Makes 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: In a large saucepan cook macaroni in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Rinse, then drain again.
In a large mixing bowl combine the cooked pasta, artichoke hearts, olives, red pepper, red onion and the cheeses.

title: surprise pudding dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In an 8 x 11-inch cake pan, melt the margarine.
Stir in the flour and the nuts.
Press mixture into a smooth layer, making sure it covers the bottom of the pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Place in the refrigerator until cool.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Shred enough lettuce to well cover bottom of bowl to be used. Sprinkle bell pepper over lettuce.
Add English peas over bell pepper.
Beat enough mayonnaise with a pinch of sugar to sweeten it, to cover English peas.
Add finely chopped eggs and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Top with bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk, stirring until thick.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add cooled milk mixture, beating well after each addition.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Divide into 12 portions and shape into balls.
Chill.
Drop onto gently boiling sauerbraten.
Cover closely and steam for about 12 minutes.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients altogether and chill.
Add pineapple, banana and nuts.

title: ding bats
directions: Cook dates, butter, sugar and egg 10 minutes slowly, then put in Rice Krispies.
Add walnuts, then cool.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: broccoli-cheese potato topper
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, Cheddar cheese, mustard and black pepper.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted, stirring often.
Add broccoli.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over potatoes.
Preparation time:
10 minutes; cook time:
10 minutes.

title: squash bake
directions: Boil squash and drain; season with salt and pepper; set aside. Put cream	cheese	and
the
margarine
in a bowl (small). Heat in microwave for a few minutes.
Beat together. Melt rest
of margarine	in
skillet; saute onion.
Put small amount of	melted margarine	in
bottom
of	baking dish; add squash.
Pour	onion over
squash.
Pour
cheese over onions. Cover with
crushed crackers.
Bake
for
minutes in 350° oven.

title: chitterlings, chittlins, mandangos
directions: Place a whole clove or ground cloves in a small saucepan; add half full with water.
Bring cloves and water to a rapid boil and let permeate the air.
Replenish water frequently while chittlins are cooking.
Also, spray the air with your choice of air fresheners.
The house smells of spices instead of the pungent odor of chittlins.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In large saucepan, simmer vinegar and sugar and then add mayonnaise.
Beat with wire whisk until smooth.
Add parsley, celery seed, mustard, green pepper, relish, tomato, celery, carrot, eggs and onion.
Blend all together.
Then add drained macaroni. Mix gently; salt and pepper to taste.
You can add more or less sugar or vinegar, depending on how tart you like it.

title: butter cookies
directions: Bake on greased pans at 350° until lightly brown on edges. Cream eggs, vanilla, butter and sugar. Gradually add your flour. Put into cookie press, then decorate with jimmies and bake.
Great for Christmas.

title: candy balls
directions: Mix well with a spoon or hands.
Roll into balls the size of cherries.
Store in the refrigerator with a sheet of wax paper between each layer.

title: chili soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and add browned ground beef.

title: roast pork ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in oven bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and seasonings.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Place ribs in bag; turn bag to coat ribs with sauce.
Arrange ribs in an even layer. Close bag, then cut 6 1/2-inch slits in top.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: In large skillet, crumble and brown sausage; remove from skillet.
Drain.
In same skillet, melt margarine.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients with sausage; mix well.
Stuff turkey loosely with stuffing immediately before roasting.
Roast turkey as directed or wrapper. Spoon remaining stuffing into greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until hot.
Makes enough to stuff a 12-pound turkey or 8 to 10 servings.

title: kasha loaf
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Boil water.
Add carrot, kasha, onion and garlic.
Cover, reduce heat and cook 20 minutes. Mix in egg and flour.
Pour in a greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlic. Add link sausage (I cook sausage first in water to get grease out). Add oregano, salt and pepper and chunk tomatoes. Cook for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Set aside to cook. Mix mayonnaise, milk, eggs, cornstarch and flour until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until set.

title: italian eggplant parmesan
directions: Season tomato sauce with garlic and basil.
Wash and cut eggplant into 1/4-inch rounds. Dip slices in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in heated oil until tender.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time; sift soda and flour. Add alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla, coconut and nuts. Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch sheet pan. Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Cool before frosting. Cake may also be baked in 3 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch layer pans for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's pound cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter.
Add vanilla, flour and milk. Preheat oven to 300° and bake for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry mixture with fork.
Add egg to sour milk; pour over dry mixture and beat.
Pat out on board.
Cut. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, vanilla, sugar and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Prepare dressing with remaining 4 ingredients.
Fold with fruit.
Chill before serving.
Adjust fruit amounts to your taste.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Roll out cookie dough.
Cut in circles and bake at 375° until done.

title: tapioca fruit salad
directions: Drain the juice from fruit into a bowl and make up to 6 cups with water, set aside. Empty the pudding into a pan, add juice and water. Cook over a low heat, stirring constantly until boiling. Remove from the heat and cool.
Add the fruit and chill over night.

title: lena's peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and margarine until it will form a soft ball in ice water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Cool for 1 hour, then cut into squares.

title: sausage mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Sprinkle sausage over croutons.
Combine eggs, milk, margarine, cheese and mustard; mix well and pour over sausage. Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 minutes.
Top with sliced mushrooms and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: mama's chili sandwich
directions: Cook Texas Pete until done.
When done, spread chili onto slices of bread.
Sprinkle on onions, then put mustard and ketchup to taste.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Roll into balls by hand. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: new mexico chili appetizer
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix all the rest with a beater and pour into pan.
Bake until knife comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve. It can also be made with meat or chicken added also.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Bone chicken breasts and remove skin.
Slice horizontally in 1/2-inch-thick slices, then cut in 1 inch squares.
Arrange on a tray.
Remove the ends and strings from fresh peas.
Wash and slice mushrooms.
Cut the green part of the onions into 1-inch lengths and then slash both ends several times making small fans, slice the white part 1/4-inch thick.
Slice bamboo shoots.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix together the crumbs, granulated sugar and butter.
Press mixture over bottom and about 1-inch up the sides of 1 (9-inch) cheesecake pan with removable bottom.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
With an electric mixer, beat sugar until blended.
Stir in pumpkin and pie spice.
Add eggs and beat well.
Pour filling into crust.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheesecake barely jiggles in center when gently shaken, about 50 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Remove pan sides; cover lightly and chill until cold, at least 3 hours or overnight.
Garnish with whipped cream and pecans.
Cut in wedges.

title: baba's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Spread in an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple-chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce and mix well.
Cover and chill.
Serve over lettuce leaves.

title: marinade for chicken and veggies
directions: Mix well; turn chicken in marinade.
Cover, put in refrigerator. Marinate 1/2 day or overnight.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken with mixture. Place chicken, skin sides down, in pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Turn; bake until done, about 15 minutes more.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Brown veal cutlets in small amount of oil.
Remove from skillet.
Drain off any remaining oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Blend well.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Mix thoroughly eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
At once, pour into unbaked pie shell.
To avoid spills, fill at oven.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake in very hot oven, 475°, for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Cool.
Serve cool or chill.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Prepare brownie mix according to packaging. Place parchment paper on 14-inch baking stone. Pour brownie mixture on paper and spread into approximately 14-inch circle. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Cool to room temperature.

title: apple cider pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Bring 1 cup cider (or juice) and sugar to boiling; add apples.
Cook, uncovered, until tender, about 8 minutes.
Drain; reserve syrup.
If needed, add cider to syrup to equal 1 1/3 cups.
Mix cornstarch, lemon juice, vanilla and 2 tablespoons cold water; stir with butter into syrup.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in apples.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry; add apple mixture. Adjust lattice top; seal.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine beans, peppers, bacon, onions, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and brown sugar in a bowl and mix well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer.

title: quiche
directions: Layer broccoli, mushrooms, bacon and cheese in pie shells. Beat eggs, half and half, salt, red and black peppers.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Insert knife in the middle; when it comes out clean, it is done.

title: best chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chinese noodle dish
directions: Combine everything, except noodles.
Place layer of noodles on bottom of casserole dish.
Add mixture of rest of ingredients, then top with the rest of the noodles.
Sprinkle almonds on top, if desired.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs
in a large bowl at medium speed of mixer for 1 minute.
Add
sugar;
beat	well.
Add
sweetened condensed milk, pudding mix and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in 1-quart of milk; pour mixture into freezer and add remaining 1/2-quart of milk.
Yield: 2 1/2 quarts.

title: crabmeat soup
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a small Dutch oven; cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Stir in whipping cream and crabmeat; heat thoroughly.
Yields 5 1/2 cups.

title: creamy hamburger casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese; set aside. Combine meat, onion, celery and green pepper. Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes until meat is done. Prepare noodles. Prepare vegetables. Mix vegetables and meat together; set aside.
Stir together tomato sauce, noodles, meat and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until tender. Top off with sliced tomatoes.

title: ida's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs one at the time. Fill powdered sugar box with flour and add to the butter, sugar, and egg mixture. Add vanilla. Grease and flour a tube cake pan (you can use Pam spray & no flour). Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove to wire rack to finish cooling.

title: pineapple scones
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients; work in shortening with 2 knives.
Add eggs well beaten (reserving a small amount of unbeaten white to brush over the top), fruit and juice.
Toss on floured board.
Pat and roll to 3/4 inch thickness as square and oblong as possible; cut into triangle shapes.
Brush with white of egg, sprinkling generously with sugar.
Bake in 450° oven 12 minutes.
Makes about 16.

title: orange bread
directions: Cook peel, water and 1 cup white sugar until peel is soft. Strain, reserving liquid.
Cook liquid and add enough milk to liquid to make 2 cups.
Mix remaining dry ingredients.
Add egg and cooled milk/liquid.
Stir well and fold in peel.
Pour into greased pans and let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
(Fill loaf pans 2/3 full.)

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening, butter, 1 cup sugar and rind.
Add eggs; mix in well.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Alternately add flour and milk to creamed mixture.
Mix well and fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Mix remaining sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over hot bread and pierce with fork.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese(microwave)
directions: Cook macaroni for 10 minutes on High.
Add 3/4 cup butter; microwave 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Blend in the flour and salt. Add the milk; stir until smooth.
Microwave 5 1/2 to 6 minutes on High, stirring with table fork every minute until thickened.
Add the grated cheese; stir until completely melted.
Stir sauce into drained macaroni; mix well.
Microwave 16 minutes on Medium, stirring every 3 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle top with paprika or buttered bread crumbs or cubes before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
When cool, debone and save broth. Mix together the deboned chicken, broth, sour cream and soups. Layer pan with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Pour mixture over cracker crumbs.
Crumble more crackers over top.
Put in oven at 350° until crackers start to turn brown.

title: olive cheese nuggets
directions: Blend cheese and butter with fork.
Add flour and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of mixture around each olive.
Roll in palm of hand to make round ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls (size of marbles).
Mash with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fake fudge
directions: Combine frosting and chips in saucepan. Melt over low heat until completely melted. Remove from stove and add nuts. Pour into 8 x 8 x 2 greased pan. Cool 2 hours. Cut into squares.

title: eggplant lasagne
directions: Peel and slice eggplant thin.
Dip eggplant into beaten egg, then bread crumbs.
Pan-fry.
Drain eggplant on paper towels. Layer as follows:
tomato sauce, lasagne, tomato sauce, eggplant and sauce. Repeat until eggplant and lasagne are finished.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with salad and Italian bread.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Put in kettle or crock-pot and cook until done.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Wash and chop lettuce.
Slice onions thinly.
In a large bowl or dish put a layer of lettuce, onions, peas, eggs, bacon bits and crabmeat.
Mix Miracle Whip and sour cream together; then spread evenly on top of layered salad.
Chill, then serve!

title: cutout sugar cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in creamed mixture at low speed until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: tempting pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in a small mixing bowl until frothy; set aside. Combine sugar and water in a 2-qt saucepan.
Place over moderate heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a full boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Gradually stir hot syrup into eggs.
Blend butter and extract into mixture.
Turn filling into a pastry (pie shell) of your choosing.
Arrange pecans of filling in desired pattern.

title: cheese and tomato casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add flour and tomatoes; cook until thickened.

title: oven omelet(from my sister, pauline)
directions: Melt
butter
in
9 x 13-inch glass pan and coat bottom and sides.
Mix
above ingredients together and place in pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Stir in milk, flour and baking powder; mix well.
Spread batter in 6 1/2 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with pie filling.
Combine lemon juice with boiling water and carefully pour over top.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until crusty top or toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chuck casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown chuck and onions in pan. Combine mushrooms, soup, milk and sauces.
Add to meat, add chestnuts and mix.
Butter 3-quart casserole dish.
Spread noodles and cover with meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese bubbles.
Remove from oven and top with Chinese noodles. Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: salami
directions: Mix together in large Tupperware or tight bowl.
Keep stored in refrigerator.
Knead every day for 5 days.
Roll into long rolls.
Bake at 150° for 10 hours.
Freezes well.

title: frozen apricot dessert
directions: Drain juice from apricots and blend in blender, adding a little juice.
Add 1/3 cup lemon juice and sugar.
Put in freezer tray.
Whip cream and add powdered sugar; put on top of apricot mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Takes about three hours to freeze.

title: fudge pie
directions: preheat oven 325°.
Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: meatballs
directions: In bowl with fork, toss together bread crumbs, salt, pepper, egg, milk and hamburger.
Shape into balls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, marshmallows and sugar; let stand overnight. Add apples, nuts and whipped cream.
Mix and chill.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Brown ground meat and drain.
Add cheese and peppers out of the can or jar.
Grease iron skillet.
Pour half of the batter into pan.
Add meat mixture, then cover with remaining batter.
Bake for 50 minutes in a 350° oven or until brown.

title: sweet chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Combine jam, soy sauce, barbecue sauce, salsa and pepper.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 325°.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix and let stand; adjust seasoning to taste.
Add milk to desired thickness.
A little chopped jalapeno makes it very good. Blue cheese may be substituted.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Make cake mix according to package.
Set aside.
Mix Ricotta cheese, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Mix well after each egg. Then add vanilla.

title: hummer
directions: Blend well until creamy.
You can use chocolate ice cream, if you want.
Pour into glass.
Top with whip cream, cherry and a little Kahlua.
Serve.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix in bowl and add the following to dry ingredients:
vanilla, egg, oil and milk.
Blend well.
Fold in frozen blueberries.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease heavy Bundt cake pan; dust with granulated sugar.
Mix ingredients well.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove cake from oven.
Punch holes in the cake with a round toothpick.
Spoon half the glaze over cake; let set for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove cake; again punch holes and use rest of glaze.

title: five gallon cream can dinner
directions: Place everything
in cream can.
Add 1 quart water to 5 gallons.
Cook
over very low fire for four hours.	When steam comes out, cover.
Cook another 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring to boil sugar, syrup and salt; add peanuts.
Cook, stirring constantly, to nearly soft ball stage, then add margarine and vanilla (and we like to add coconut).
Continue cooking to very hard crack stage.
Now, stir in soda and pour immediately on cookie sheet.
Spread as thin as you prefer.
It will be very thick and amber colored.
When cool, break into pieces.
This is our favorite brittle recipe.
It is also good with black walnuts or pecans instead of peanuts.
Have a large cookie sheet, sprayed or coated with butter ready for candy mixture.
My husband usually makes this brittle while I cook other kinds.

title: brontosaurus ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients except spareribs.
Marinate ribs in sauce overnight.
Remove from marinade and bake at 300° to 325° until tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May also be done on barbecue grill or in smoker.
Baste often during cooking with marinade.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in microwave-safe dish.
Add 8 ounces of water. Cook thoroughly 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool, debone and dice.
In Dutch oven, cook all remaining ingredients except noodles.
Add chicken and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add noodles.
Serve when noodles are fully cooked.

title: chicken breasts pecan
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with meat tenderizer.
Season flour with salt and pepper.
Dust chicken breasts with flour.
Dip into beaten eggs.
Bread with ground pecans.
Heat butter in skillet. Add chicken breasts; saute over medium heat until browned.
Put in baking pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: oven parmesan chips
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices; place on greased baking sheet in single layer.
Mix butter, onion, salt and pepper; brush each side.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender and golden.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with a fresh vegetable platter.

title: black-eyed peas and polish sausage
directions: Brown the sausage and green pepper and drain.
Put in cooktop casserole with the rice, water, mushrooms and onion. Simmer 20 minutes and add the black-eyed peas.
Simmer 20 minutes more and serve with salad and crusty French bread.

title: jerusalem potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes and place in baking pan. Add chopped onion and melted margarine. Sprinkle other ingredients over potatoes. Bake at 350° until done, then broil until brown.

title: salmon croquettes for two
directions: The day before serving, drain and remove bones from salmon. Break salmon into small pieces with a fork.
Add salt, lemon juice, egg, 1 tablespoon melted oleo and Worcestershire sauce; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 4 patties, wrap in plastic wrap or aluminum foil, place in the refrigerator overnight.
The next day crush enough cornflakes to make a cup of fine crumbs.
Roll patties in cornflake crumbs and saute in melted oleo until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: birthday cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together. Cream shortening and sugar. Add alternately the flour and the milk. Last, fold in the beaten egg whites. Bake in a large pan in a moderate oven at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix all together in a large pot and heat. Ready to serve.

title: done-buttered biscuits
directions: Mix all together and fill muffin tins about 3/4 full and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: mexican-style deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise and remove yolks.
Place yolks in a bowl; mash with a fork.
Add mayonnaise, green chili peppers, olives, chili powder and red pepper to yolk mixture.
Mix well.
Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture.
Garnish with sliced pitted ripe olives or cilantro and serve with salsa, if desired.

title: banana cake
directions: Dissolve soda and vanilla in hot water.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and banana.
Beat well. Add buttermilk and nuts, alternating with flour which has been sifted with salt and baking powder.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Dissolve soda in water and add to mix with lemon juice. Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, 400° for 4 minutes and finish at 350° for 19 minutes.
Total cooking time:
30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in bread and pineapple.
Put in unbuttered baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Let cool slightly before serving with ham.

title: triple layer brownies
directions: First Layer:
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, blending well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: spiced carrot snack cake
directions: Grease bottom of an 8 or 9 inch square pan.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in bottom of baking dish. Cover with sour cream and soup mixed together.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter, then poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mama's cool coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions on box; bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Fork holes in cake when it is done.
In saucepan, mix and boil for 8 minutes the milk, sugar and 1 (6-ounce) package of coconut.
Pour mixture over hot cake.
Cover; cool in refrigerator.
When cool, spread Cool Whip on cake and sprinkle with other package of coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: nut cake
directions: Boil the sugar, raisins, water and margarine for 3 minutes. Let cool.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and walnuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pineapple jello mold
directions: Thaw strawberries just before using.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold.
Put into refrigerator until set.
Cover with sour cream, then pour in remaining fruit mixture. Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 6.

title: pennsylvania milk punch
directions: Soften ice cream and sherbet.
Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Serve immediately.
An ice ring of equal parts pineapple and orange juice and water may be used if desired. Flavor of sherbet determines color of punch.
Serves 20 (4 quarts).

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones and flake the salmon.
Add soft bread crumbs, onion and salt.
Beat eggs and milk together; add to other ingredients.
After mixing well, put in small loaf pan (about 8 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) or bake dish sprayed with Pam.
Set in shallow pan of hot water.
Bake in 375° oven for 1/2 to 3/4 of an hour or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serve with white sauce.

title: chef's cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Stir in melted butter.
Pack firmly in 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: buffet scalloped carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
In saucepan in margarine, gently cook onion for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk and cook until smooth.
In 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of carrots, then layers of cheese, repeating until both are used, ending with carrots.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with bread crumbs, seasoned with sage.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: best little barbecue sauce in saugus
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate 1 hour before using. Good for ribs and chicken.

title: easy salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, potatoes, egg, salt and pepper together well; include salmon liquid.
Stir in enough cracker crumbs to hold mixture together.
Shape into flat cakes.
Fry in oil until lightly brown.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with thick white sauce or gravy.

title: molded cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Let cool. Add remaining ingredients. Put in mold. Let chill over night. Unmold unto plate.

title: bus driver drink
directions: Blend all ingredients in the blender until frothy.
Drink on the way to the school bus.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients and set aside.

title: apple slaw(if you like apples, you'll like this slaw recipe.)
directions: Wash cabbage, pull larger leaves off and save.
Cut up cabbage center.
Cut, but do not peel apples, into cubes.
Save 1/2 an apple for garnish.
Chill apples and cabbage.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and beat vigorously while dough is forming. Drop dough by heaping tablespoons onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine 1/4 cup butter or margarine melted with 1 teaspoon garlic powder.
Brush over biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Saut onions. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 hours or all afternoon in a large crock-pot or roaster. Salt to taste.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix sauerkraut, 1 cup crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, salt and egg.
Form into 16 balls.
Roll in remaining crumbs.
Brown in oleo until golden.
Serve with
ham.
Yields 8 servings.

title: italian-style lamb shanks
directions: In Dutch oven heat oil and garlic.
Salt and pepper lamb shanks.
Brown shanks in oil and garlic; drain excess oil and remove garlic.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce to lamb shanks.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, depending on how well cooked you like your veggies.
Add strips of onion and green pepper to pot 1/2 hour to 45 minutes before end of cooking time. Also cook pasta at this time.
Serve lamb shanks and pour the sauce and veggies over pasta.
